var book = {
	"name": "Psalm",
	"numChapters": 150,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Oh, the joys of those who do notfollow the advice of the wicked,or stand around with sinners,or join in with mockers.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But they delight in the law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,meditating on it day and night.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They are like trees planted along the riverbank,bearing fruit each season.Their leaves never wither,and they prosper in all they do.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But not the wicked!They are like worthless chaff, scattered by the wind.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They will be condemned at the time of judgment.Sinners will have no place among the godly.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> watches over the path of the godly,but the path of the wicked leads to destruction."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Why are the nations so angry?Why do they waste their time with futile plans?",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The kings of the earth prepare for battle;the rulers plot togetheragainst the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>and against his anointed one.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Let us break their chains,” they cry,“and free ourselves from slavery to God.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But the one who rules in heaven laughs.The Lord scoffs at them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then in anger he rebukes them,terrifying them with his fierce fury.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For the Lord declares, “I have placed my chosen king on the thronein Jerusalem, on my holy mountain.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The king proclaims the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s decree:“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, ‘You are my son.Today I have become your Father.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Only ask, and I will give you the nations as your inheritance,the whole earth as your possession.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You will break them with an iron rodand smash them like clay pots.’”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now then, you kings, act wisely!Be warned, you rulers of the earth!",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with reverent fear,and rejoice with trembling.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Submit to God’s royal son, or he will become angry,and you will be destroyed in the midst of all your activities—for his anger flares up in an instant.But what joy for all who take refuge in him!"
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, I have so many enemies;so many are against me.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So many are saying,“God will never rescue him!” <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, are a shield around me;you are my glory, the one who holds my head high.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I cried out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,and he answered me from his holy mountain. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I lay down and slept,yet I woke up in safety,for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was watching over me.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I am not afraid of ten thousand enemieswho surround me on every side.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Arise, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!Rescue me, my God!Slap all my enemies in the face!Shatter the teeth of the wicked!",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Victory comes from you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.May you bless your people. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>"
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Answer me when I call to you,O God who declares me innocent.Free me from my troubles.Have mercy on me and hear my prayer.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>How long will you people ruin my reputation?How long will you make groundless accusations?How long will you continue your lies? <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You can be sure of this:The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> set apart the godly for himself.The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will answer when I call to him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Don’t sin by letting anger control you.Think about it overnight and remain silent. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Offer sacrifices in the right spirit,and trust the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Many people say, “Who will show us better times?”Let your face smile on us, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>You have given me greater joythan those who have abundant harvests of grain and new wine.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>In peace I will lie down and sleep,for you alone, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, will keep me safe."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, hear me as I pray;pay attention to my groaning.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Listen to my cry for help, my King and my God,for I pray to no one but you.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Listen to my voice in the morning, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.Each morning I bring my requests to you and wait expectantly.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>O God, you take no pleasure in wickedness;you cannot tolerate the sins of the wicked.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Therefore, the proud may not stand in your presence,for you hate all who do evil.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You will destroy those who tell lies.The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> detests murderers and deceivers.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Because of your unfailing love, I can enter your house;I will worship at your Temple with deepest awe.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Lead me in the right path, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,or my enemies will conquer me.Make your way plain for me to follow.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>My enemies cannot speak a truthful word.Their deepest desire is to destroy others.Their talk is foul, like the stench from an open grave.Their tongues are filled with flattery.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>O God, declare them guilty.Let them be caught in their own traps.Drive them away because of their many sins,for they have rebelled against you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But let all who take refuge in you rejoice;let them sing joyful praises forever.Spread your protection over them,that all who love your name may be filled with joy.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For you bless the godly, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;you surround them with your shield of love."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, don’t rebuke me in your angeror discipline me in your rage.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Have compassion on me, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for I am weak.Heal me, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for my bones are in agony.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I am sick at heart.How long, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, until you restore me?",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Return, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and rescue me.Save me because of your unfailing love.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For the dead do not remember you.Who can praise you from the grave?",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I am worn out from sobbing.All night I flood my bed with weeping,drenching it with my tears.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>My vision is blurred by grief;my eyes are worn out because of all my enemies.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Go away, all you who do evil,for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has heard my weeping.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has heard my plea;the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will answer my prayer.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>May all my enemies be disgraced and terrified.May they suddenly turn back in shame."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>I come to you for protection, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God.Save me from my persecutors—rescue me!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>If you don’t, they will maul me like a lion,tearing me to pieces with no one to rescue me.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, if I have done wrongor am guilty of injustice,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>if I have betrayed a friendor plundered my enemy without cause,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>then let my enemies capture me.Let them trample me into the groundand drag my honor in the dust. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Arise, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, in anger!Stand up against the fury of my enemies!Wake up, my God, and bring justice!",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Gather the nations before you.Rule over them from on high.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> judges the nations.Declare me righteous, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,for I am innocent, O Most High!",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>End the evil of those who are wicked,and defend the righteous.For you look deep within the mind and heart,O righteous God.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>God is my shield,saving those whose hearts are true and right.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>God is an honest judge.He is angry with the wicked every day.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>If a person does not repent,God will sharpen his sword;he will bend and string his bow.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He will prepare his deadly weaponsand shoot his flaming arrows.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The wicked conceive evil;they are pregnant with troubleand give birth to lies.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>They dig a deep pit to trap others,then fall into it themselves.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The trouble they make for others backfires on them.The violence they plan falls on their own heads.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I will thank the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> because he is just;I will sing praise to the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Most High."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, our Lord, your majestic name fills the earth!Your glory is higher than the heavens.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>You have taught children and infantsto tell of your strength,silencing your enemiesand all who oppose you.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When I look at the night sky and see the work of your fingers—the moon and the stars you set in place—",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>what are mere mortals that you should think about them,human beings that you should care for them?",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Yet you made them only a little lower than Godand crowned them with glory and honor.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You gave them charge of everything you made,putting all things under their authority—",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>the flocks and the herdsand all the wild animals,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>the birds in the sky, the fish in the sea,and everything that swims the ocean currents.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, our Lord, your majestic name fills the earth!"
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>I will praise you, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, with all my heart;I will tell of all the marvelous things you have done.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I will be filled with joy because of you.I will sing praises to your name, O Most High.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>My enemies retreated;they staggered and died when you appeared.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For you have judged in my favor;from your throne you have judged with fairness.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You have rebuked the nations and destroyed the wicked;you have erased their names forever.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The enemy is finished, in endless ruins;the cities you uprooted are now forgotten.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> reigns forever,executing judgment from his throne.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He will judge the world with justiceand rule the nations with fairness.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is a shelter for the oppressed,a refuge in times of trouble.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Those who know your name trust in you,for you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, do not abandon those who search for you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Sing praises to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who reigns in Jerusalem.Tell the world about his unforgettable deeds.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For he who avenges murder cares for the helpless.He does not ignore the cries of those who suffer.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, have mercy on me.See how my enemies torment me.Snatch me back from the jaws of death.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Save me so I can praise you publicly at Jerusalem’s gates,so I can rejoice that you have rescued me.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The nations have fallen into the pit they dug for others.Their own feet have been caught in the trap they set.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is known for his justice.The wicked are trapped by their own deeds. <span class=\"selah\">Quiet Interlude</span>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The wicked will go down to the grave.This is the fate of all the nations who ignore God.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But the needy will not be ignored forever;the hopes of the poor will not always be crushed.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Arise, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!Do not let mere mortals defy you!Judge the nations!",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Make them tremble in fear, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.Let the nations know they are merely human. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>"
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, why do you stand so far away?Why do you hide when I am in trouble?",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The wicked arrogantly hunt down the poor.Let them be caught in the evil they plan for others.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For they brag about their evil desires;they praise the greedy and curse the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The wicked are too proud to seek God.They seem to think that God is dead.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Yet they succeed in everything they do.They do not see your punishment awaiting them.They sneer at all their enemies.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They think, “Nothing bad will ever happen to us!We will be free of trouble forever!”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Their mouths are full of cursing, lies, and threats.Trouble and evil are on the tips of their tongues.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They lurk in ambush in the villages,waiting to murder innocent people.They are always searching for helpless victims.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Like lions crouched in hiding,they wait to pounce on the helpless.Like hunters they capture the helplessand drag them away in nets.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Their helpless victims are crushed;they fall beneath the strength of the wicked.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The wicked think, “God isn’t watching us!He has closed his eyes and won’t even see what we do!”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Arise, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!Punish the wicked, O God!Do not ignore the helpless!",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Why do the wicked get away with despising God?They think, “God will never call us to account.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But you see the trouble and grief they cause.You take note of it and punish them.The helpless put their trust in you.You defend the orphans.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Break the arms of these wicked, evil people!Go after them until the last one is destroyed.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is king forever and ever!The godless nations will vanish from the land.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you know the hopes of the helpless.Surely you will hear their cries and comfort them.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>You will bring justice to the orphans and the oppressed,so mere people can no longer terrify them."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>I trust in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for protection.So why do you say to me,“Fly like a bird to the mountains for safety!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The wicked are stringing their bowsand fitting their arrows on the bowstrings.They shoot from the shadowsat those whose hearts are right.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The foundations of law and order have collapsed.What can the righteous do?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is in his holy Temple;the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> still rules from heaven.He watches everyone closely,examining every person on earth.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> examines both the righteous and the wicked.He hates those who love violence.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He will rain down blazing coals and burning sulfur on the wicked,punishing them with scorching winds.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For the righteous <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> loves justice.The virtuous will see his face."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Help, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for the godly are fast disappearing!The faithful have vanished from the earth!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Neighbors lie to each other,speaking with flattering lips and deceitful hearts.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> cut off their flattering lipsand silence their boastful tongues.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They say, “We will lie to our hearts’ content.Our lips are our own—who can stop us?”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> replies, “I have seen violence done to the helpless,and I have heard the groans of the poor.Now I will rise up to rescue them,as they have longed for me to do.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s promises are pure,like silver refined in a furnace,purified seven times over.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Therefore, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, we know you will protect the oppressed,preserving them forever from this lying generation,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>even though the wicked strut about,and evil is praised throughout the land."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, how long will you forget me? Forever?How long will you look the other way?",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>How long must I struggle with anguish in my soul,with sorrow in my heart every day?How long will my enemy have the upper hand?",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Turn and answer me, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God!Restore the sparkle to my eyes, or I will die.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Don’t let my enemies gloat, saying, “We have defeated him!”Don’t let them rejoice at my downfall.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But I trust in your unfailing love.I will rejoice because you have rescued me.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I will sing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>because he is good to me."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Only fools say in their hearts,“There is no God.”They are corrupt, and their actions are evil;not one of them does good!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> looks down from heavenon the entire human race;he looks to see if anyone is truly wise,if anyone seeks God.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But no, all have turned away;all have become corrupt.No one does good,not a single one!",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Will those who do evil never learn?They eat up my people like breadand wouldn’t think of praying to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Terror will grip them,for God is with those who obey him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The wicked frustrate the plans of the oppressed,but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will protect his people.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Who will come from Mount Zion to rescue Israel?When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> restores his people,Jacob will shout with joy, and Israel will rejoice."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Who may worship in your sanctuary, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?Who may enter your presence on your holy hill?",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Those who lead blameless lives and do what is right,speaking the truth from sincere hearts.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Those who refuse to gossipor harm their neighborsor speak evil of their friends.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Those who despise flagrant sinners,and honor the faithful followers of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,and keep their promises even when it hurts.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Those who lend money without charging interest,and who cannot be bribed to lie about the innocent.Such people will stand firm forever."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Keep me safe, O God,for I have come to you for refuge.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “You are my Master!Every good thing I have comes from you.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The godly people in the landare my true heroes!I take pleasure in them!",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Troubles multiply for those who chase after other gods.I will not take part in their sacrifices of bloodor even speak the names of their gods.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you alone are my inheritance, my cup of blessing.You guard all that is mine.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The land you have given me is a pleasant land.What a wonderful inheritance!",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I will bless the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who guides me;even at night my heart instructs me.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I know the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is always with me.I will not be shaken, for he is right beside me.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>No wonder my heart is glad, and I rejoice.My body rests in safety.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For you will not leave my soul among the deador allow your holy one to rot in the grave.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You will show me the way of life,granting me the joy of your presenceand the pleasures of living with you forever."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, hear my plea for justice.Listen to my cry for help.Pay attention to my prayer,for it comes from honest lips.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Declare me innocent,for you see those who do right.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You have tested my thoughts and examined my heart in the night.You have scrutinized me and found nothing wrong.I am determined not to sin in what I say.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I have followed your commands,which keep me from following cruel and evil people.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>My steps have stayed on your path;I have not wavered from following you.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I am praying to you because I know you will answer, O God.Bend down and listen as I pray.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Show me your unfailing love in wonderful ways.By your mighty power you rescuethose who seek refuge from their enemies.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Guard me as you would guard your own eyes.Hide me in the shadow of your wings.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Protect me from wicked people who attack me,from murderous enemies who surround me.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They are without pity.Listen to their boasting!",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They track me down and surround me,watching for the chance to throw me to the ground.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They are like hungry lions, eager to tear me apart—like young lions hiding in ambush.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Arise, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!Stand against them, and bring them to their knees!Rescue me from the wicked with your sword!",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>By the power of your hand, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,destroy those who look to this world for their reward.But satisfy the hunger of your treasured ones.May their children have plenty,leaving an inheritance for their descendants.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Because I am righteous, I will see you.When I awake, I will see you face to face and be satisfied."
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>I love you, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;you are my strength.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is my rock, my fortress, and my savior;my God is my rock, in whom I find protection.He is my shield, the power that saves me,and my place of safety.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I called on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who is worthy of praise,and he saved me from my enemies.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The ropes of death entangled me;floods of destruction swept over me.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The grave wrapped its ropes around me;death laid a trap in my path.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But in my distress I cried out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;yes, I prayed to my God for help.He heard me from his sanctuary;my cry to him reached his ears.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then the earth quaked and trembled.The foundations of the mountains shook;they quaked because of his anger.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Smoke poured from his nostrils;fierce flames leaped from his mouth.Glowing coals blazed forth from him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He opened the heavens and came down;dark storm clouds were beneath his feet.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Mounted on a mighty angelic being, he flew,soaring on the wings of the wind.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He shrouded himself in darkness,veiling his approach with dark rain clouds.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Thick clouds shielded the brightness around himand rained down hail and burning coals.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> thundered from heaven;the voice of the Most High resoundedamid the hail and burning coals.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He shot his arrows and scattered his enemies;great bolts of lightning flashed, and they were confused.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then at your command, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,at the blast of your breath,the bottom of the sea could be seen,and the foundations of the earth were laid bare.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He reached down from heaven and rescued me;he drew me out of deep waters.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He rescued me from my powerful enemies,from those who hated me and were too strong for me.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They attacked me at a moment when I was in distress,but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> supported me.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He led me to a place of safety;he rescued me because he delights in me.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rewarded me for doing right;he restored me because of my innocence.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>For I have kept the ways of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;I have not turned from my God to follow evil.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>I have followed all his regulations;I have never abandoned his decrees.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>I am blameless before God;I have kept myself from sin.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rewarded me for doing right.He has seen my innocence.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>To the faithful you show yourself faithful;to those with integrity you show integrity.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>To the pure you show yourself pure,but to the crooked you show yourself shrewd.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>You rescue the humble,but you humiliate the proud.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>You light a lamp for me.The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, my God, lights up my darkness.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>In your strength I can crush an army;with my God I can scale any wall.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>God’s way is perfect.All the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s promises prove true.He is a shield for all who look to him for protection.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>For who is God except the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?Who but our God is a solid rock?",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>God arms me with strength,and he makes my way perfect.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He makes me as surefooted as a deer,enabling me to stand on mountain heights.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>He trains my hands for battle;he strengthens my arm to draw a bronze bow.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>You have given me your shield of victory.Your right hand supports me;your help has made me great.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>You have made a wide path for my feetto keep them from slipping.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>I chased my enemies and caught them;I did not stop until they were conquered.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>I struck them down so they could not get up;they fell beneath my feet.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>You have armed me with strength for the battle;you have subdued my enemies under my feet.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>You placed my foot on their necks.I have destroyed all who hated me.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>They called for help, but no one came to their rescue.They even cried to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but he refused to answer.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>I ground them as fine as dust in the wind.I swept them into the gutter like dirt.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>You gave me victory over my accusers.You appointed me ruler over nations;people I don’t even know now serve me.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>As soon as they hear of me, they submit;foreign nations cringe before me.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>They all lose their courageand come trembling from their strongholds.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives! Praise to my Rock!May the God of my salvation be exalted!",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>He is the God who pays back those who harm me;he subdues the nations under me",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>and rescues me from my enemies.You hold me safe beyond the reach of my enemies;you save me from violent opponents.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>For this, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, I will praise you among the nations;I will sing praises to your name.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>You give great victories to your king;you show unfailing love to your anointed,to David and all his descendants forever."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>The heavens proclaim the glory of God.The skies display his craftsmanship.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Day after day they continue to speak;night after night they make him known.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They speak without a sound or word;their voice is never heard.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Yet their message has gone throughout the earth,and their words to all the world.God has made a home in the heavens for the sun.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>It bursts forth like a radiant bridegroom after his wedding.It rejoices like a great athlete eager to run the race.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The sun rises at one end of the heavensand follows its course to the other end.Nothing can hide from its heat.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The instructions of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> are perfect,reviving the soul.The decrees of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> are trustworthy,making wise the simple.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> are right,bringing joy to the heart.The commands of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> are clear,giving insight for living.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Reverence for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is pure,lasting forever.The laws of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> are true;each one is fair.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They are more desirable than gold,even the finest gold.They are sweeter than honey,even honey dripping from the comb.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They are a warning to your servant,a great reward for those who obey them.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>How can I know all the sins lurking in my heart?Cleanse me from these hidden faults.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Keep your servant from deliberate sins!Don’t let them control me.Then I will be free of guiltand innocent of great sin.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>May the words of my mouthand the meditation of my heartbe pleasing to you,O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, my rock and my redeemer."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>In times of trouble, may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> answer your cry.May the name of the God of Jacob keep you safe from all harm.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>May he send you help from his sanctuaryand strengthen you from Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>May he remember all your giftsand look favorably on your burnt offerings. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>May he grant your heart’s desiresand make all your plans succeed.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>May we shout for joy when we hear of your victoryand raise a victory banner in the name of our God.May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> answer all your prayers.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now I know that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rescues his anointed king.He will answer him from his holy heavenand rescue him by his great power.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Some nations boast of their chariots and horses,but we boast in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Those nations will fall down and collapse,but we will rise up and stand firm.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Give victory to our king, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!Answer our cry for help."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>How the king rejoices in your strength, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!He shouts with joy because you give him victory.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>For you have given him his heart’s desire;you have withheld nothing he requested. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You welcomed him back with success and prosperity.You placed a crown of finest gold on his head.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He asked you to preserve his life,and you granted his request.The days of his life stretch on forever.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Your victory brings him great honor,and you have clothed him with splendor and majesty.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You have endowed him with eternal blessingsand given him the joy of your presence.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For the king trusts in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.The unfailing love of the Most High will keep him from stumbling.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You will capture all your enemies.Your strong right hand will seize all who hate you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You will throw them in a flaming furnacewhen you appear.The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will consume them in his anger;fire will devour them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You will wipe their children from the face of the earth;they will never have descendants.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Although they plot against you,their evil schemes will never succeed.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For they will turn and runwhen they see your arrows aimed at them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Rise up, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, in all your power.With music and singing we celebrate your mighty acts."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>My God, my God, why have you abandoned me?Why are you so far away when I groan for help?",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Every day I call to you, my God, but you do not answer.Every night I lift my voice, but I find no relief.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Yet you are holy,enthroned on the praises of Israel.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Our ancestors trusted in you,and you rescued them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They cried out to you and were saved.They trusted in you and were never disgraced.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But I am a worm and not a man.I am scorned and despised by all!",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Everyone who sees me mocks me.They sneer and shake their heads, saying,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“Is this the one who relies on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?Then let the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> save him!If the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> loves him so much,let the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rescue him!”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Yet you brought me safely from my mother’s womband led me to trust you at my mother’s breast.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>I was thrust into your arms at my birth.You have been my God from the moment I was born.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Do not stay so far from me,for trouble is near,and no one else can help me.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>My enemies surround me like a herd of bulls;fierce bulls of Bashan have hemmed me in!",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Like lions they open their jaws against me,roaring and tearing into their prey.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>My life is poured out like water,and all my bones are out of joint.My heart is like wax,melting within me.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>My strength has dried up like sunbaked clay.My tongue sticks to the roof of my mouth.You have laid me in the dust and left me for dead.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>My enemies surround me like a pack of dogs;an evil gang closes in on me.They have pierced my hands and feet.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I can count all my bones.My enemies stare at me and gloat.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They divide my garments among themselvesand throw dice for my clothing.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, do not stay far away!You are my strength; come quickly to my aid!",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Save me from the sword;spare my precious life from these dogs.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Snatch me from the lion’s jawsand from the horns of these wild oxen.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>I will proclaim your name to my brothers and sisters.I will praise you among your assembled people.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, all you who fear him!Honor him, all you descendants of Jacob!Show him reverence, all you descendants of Israel!",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>For he has not ignored or belittled the suffering of the needy.He has not turned his back on them,but has listened to their cries for help.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>I will praise you in the great assembly.I will fulfill my vows in the presence of those who worship you.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The poor will eat and be satisfied.All who seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will praise him.Their hearts will rejoice with everlasting joy.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The whole earth will acknowledge the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and return to him.All the families of the nations will bow down before him.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>For royal power belongs to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.He rules all the nations.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Let the rich of the earth feast and worship.Bow before him, all who are mortal,all whose lives will end as dust.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Our children will also serve him.Future generations will hear about the wonders of the Lord.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>His righteous acts will be told to those not yet born.They will hear about everything he has done."
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is my shepherd;I have all that I need.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He lets me rest in green meadows;he leads me beside peaceful streams.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>He renews my strength.He guides me along right paths,bringing honor to his name.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Even when I walkthrough the darkest valley,I will not be afraid,for you are close beside me.Your rod and your staffprotect and comfort me.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You prepare a feast for mein the presence of my enemies.You honor me by anointing my head with oil.My cup overflows with blessings.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Surely your goodness and unfailing love will pursue meall the days of my life,and I will live in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>forever."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>The earth is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s, and everything in it.The world and all its people belong to him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>For he laid the earth’s foundation on the seasand built it on the ocean depths.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Who may climb the mountain of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?Who may stand in his holy place?",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Only those whose hands and hearts are pure,who do not worship idolsand never tell lies.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They will receive the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s blessingand have a right relationship with God their savior.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Such people may seek youand worship in your presence, O God of Jacob. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Open up, ancient gates!Open up, ancient doors,and let the King of glory enter.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Who is the King of glory?The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, strong and mighty;the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, invincible in battle.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Open up, ancient gates!Open up, ancient doors,and let the King of glory enter.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Who is the King of glory?The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of Heaven’s Armies—he is the King of glory. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>"
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, I give my life to you.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>I trust in you, my God!Do not let me be disgraced,or let my enemies rejoice in my defeat.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>No one who trusts in you will ever be disgraced,but disgrace comes to those who try to deceive others.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Show me the right path, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;point out the road for me to follow.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Lead me by your truth and teach me,for you are the God who saves me.All day long I put my hope in you.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Remember, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, your compassion and unfailing love,which you have shown from long ages past.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Do not remember the rebellious sins of my youth.Remember me in the light of your unfailing love,for you are merciful, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is good and does what is right;he shows the proper path to those who go astray.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He leads the humble in doing right,teaching them his way.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> leads with unfailing love and faithfulnessall who keep his covenant and obey his demands.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>For the honor of your name, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,forgive my many, many sins.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Who are those who fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?He will show them the path they should choose.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>They will live in prosperity,and their children will inherit the land.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is a friend to those who fear him.He teaches them his covenant.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>My eyes are always on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,for he rescues me from the traps of my enemies.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Turn to me and have mercy,for I am alone and in deep distress.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>My problems go from bad to worse.Oh, save me from them all!",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Feel my pain and see my trouble.Forgive all my sins.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>See how many enemies I haveand how viciously they hate me!",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Protect me! Rescue my life from them!Do not let me be disgraced, for in you I take refuge.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>May integrity and honesty protect me,for I put my hope in you.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>O God, ransom Israelfrom all its troubles."
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Declare me innocent, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,for I have acted with integrity;I have trusted in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> without wavering.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Put me on trial, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and cross-examine me.Test my motives and my heart.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For I am always aware of your unfailing love,and I have lived according to your truth.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I do not spend time with liarsor go along with hypocrites.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I hate the gatherings of those who do evil,and I refuse to join in with the wicked.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I wash my hands to declare my innocence.I come to your altar, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>singing a song of thanksgivingand telling of all your wonders.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I love your sanctuary, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,the place where your glorious presence dwells.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Don’t let me suffer the fate of sinners.Don’t condemn me along with murderers.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Their hands are dirty with evil schemes,and they constantly take bribes.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But I am not like that; I live with integrity.So redeem me and show me mercy.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now I stand on solid ground,and I will publicly praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is my light and my salvation—so why should I be afraid?The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is my fortress, protecting me from danger,so why should I tremble?",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When evil people come to devour me,when my enemies and foes attack me,they will stumble and fall.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Though a mighty army surrounds me,my heart will not be afraid.Even if I am attacked,I will remain confident.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The one thing I ask of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—the thing I seek most—is to live in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> all the days of my life,delighting in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s perfectionsand meditating in his Temple.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For he will conceal me there when troubles come;he will hide me in his sanctuary.He will place me out of reach on a high rock.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then I will hold my head highabove my enemies who surround me.At his sanctuary I will offer sacrifices with shouts of joy,singing and praising the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with music.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Hear me as I pray, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.Be merciful and answer me!",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>My heart has heard you say, “Come and talk with me.”And my heart responds, “<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, I am coming.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Do not turn your back on me.Do not reject your servant in anger.You have always been my helper.Don’t leave me now; don’t abandon me,O God of my salvation!",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Even if my father and mother abandon me,the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will hold me close.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Teach me how to live, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.Lead me along the right path,for my enemies are waiting for me.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Do not let me fall into their hands.For they accuse me of things I’ve never done;with every breath they threaten me with violence.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Yet I am confident I will see the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s goodnesswhile I am here in the land of the living.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Wait patiently for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.Be brave and courageous.Yes, wait patiently for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"28": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>I pray to you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, my rock.Do not turn a deaf ear to me.For if you are silent,I might as well give up and die.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Listen to my prayer for mercyas I cry out to you for help,as I lift my hands toward your holy sanctuary.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Do not drag me away with the wicked—with those who do evil—those who speak friendly words to their neighborswhile planning evil in their hearts.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Give them the punishment they so richly deserve!Measure it out in proportion to their wickedness.Pay them back for all their evil deeds!Give them a taste of what they have done to others.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They care nothing for what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has doneor for what his hands have made.So he will tear them down,and they will never be rebuilt!",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!For he has heard my cry for mercy.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is my strength and shield.I trust him with all my heart.He helps me, and my heart is filled with joy.I burst out in songs of thanksgiving.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gives his people strength.He is a safe fortress for his anointed king.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Save your people!Bless Israel, your special possession.Lead them like a shepherd,and carry them in your arms forever."
		},
		"29": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Honor the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you heavenly beings;honor the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for his glory and strength.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Honor the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for the glory of his name.Worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the splendor of his holiness.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> echoes above the sea.The God of glory thunders.The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> thunders over the mighty sea.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is powerful;the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is majestic.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> splits the mighty cedars;the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shatters the cedars of Lebanon.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He makes Lebanon’s mountains skip like a calf;he makes Mount Hermon leap like a young wild ox.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> strikeswith bolts of lightning.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> makes the barren wilderness quake;the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shakes the wilderness of Kadesh.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> twists mighty oaksand strips the forests bare.In his Temple everyone shouts, “Glory!”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rules over the floodwaters.The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> reigns as king forever.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gives his people strength.The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> blesses them with peace."
		},
		"30": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>I will exalt you, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for you rescued me.You refused to let my enemies triumph over me.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, I cried to you for help,and you restored my health.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You brought me up from the grave, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.You kept me from falling into the pit of death.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Sing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, all you godly ones!Praise his holy name.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For his anger lasts only a moment,but his favor lasts a lifetime!Weeping may last through the night,but joy comes with the morning.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When I was prosperous, I said,“Nothing can stop me now!”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Your favor, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, made me as secure as a mountain.Then you turned away from me, and I was shattered.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I cried out to you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.I begged the Lord for mercy, saying,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“What will you gain if I die,if I sink into the grave?Can my dust praise you?Can it tell of your faithfulness?",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Hear me, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and have mercy on me.Help me, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You have turned my mourning into joyful dancing.You have taken away my clothes of mourning and clothed me with joy,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>that I might sing praises to you and not be silent.O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, I will give you thanks forever!"
		},
		"31": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, I have come to you for protection;don’t let me be disgraced.Save me, for you do what is right.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Turn your ear to listen to me;rescue me quickly.Be my rock of protection,a fortress where I will be safe.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You are my rock and my fortress.For the honor of your name, lead me out of this danger.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Pull me from the trap my enemies set for me,for I find protection in you alone.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I entrust my spirit into your hand.Rescue me, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for you are a faithful God.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I hate those who worship worthless idols.I trust in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I will be glad and rejoice in your unfailing love,for you have seen my troubles,and you care about the anguish of my soul.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You have not handed me over to my enemiesbut have set me in a safe place.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Have mercy on me, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for I am in distress.Tears blur my eyes.My body and soul are withering away.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>I am dying from grief;my years are shortened by sadness.Sin has drained my strength;I am wasting away from within.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>I am scorned by all my enemiesand despised by my neighbors—even my friends are afraid to come near me.When they see me on the street,they run the other way.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>I am ignored as if I were dead,as if I were a broken pot.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I have heard the many rumors about me,and I am surrounded by terror.My enemies conspire against me,plotting to take my life.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But I am trusting you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,saying, “You are my God!”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>My future is in your hands.Rescue me from those who hunt me down relentlessly.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Let your favor shine on your servant.In your unfailing love, rescue me.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Don’t let me be disgraced, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,for I call out to you for help.Let the wicked be disgraced;let them lie silent in the grave.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Silence their lying lips—those proud and arrogant lips that accuse the godly.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>How great is the goodnessyou have stored up for those who fear you.You lavish it on those who come to you for protection,blessing them before the watching world.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You hide them in the shelter of your presence,safe from those who conspire against them.You shelter them in your presence,far from accusing tongues.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,for he has shown me the wonders of his unfailing love.He kept me safe when my city was under attack.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>In panic I cried out,“I am cut off from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!”But you heard my cry for mercyand answered my call for help.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Love the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, all you godly ones!For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> protects those who are loyal to him,but he harshly punishes the arrogant.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So be strong and courageous,all you who put your hope in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!"
		},
		"32": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Oh, what joy for thosewhose disobedience is forgiven,whose sin is put out of sight!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Yes, what joy for thosewhose record the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has cleared of guilt,whose lives are lived in complete honesty!",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When I refused to confess my sin,my body wasted away,and I groaned all day long.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Day and night your hand of discipline was heavy on me.My strength evaporated like water in the summer heat. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Finally, I confessed all my sins to youand stopped trying to hide my guilt.I said to myself, “I will confess my rebellion to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”And you forgave me! All my guilt is gone. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Therefore, let all the godly pray to you while there is still time,that they may not drown in the floodwaters of judgment.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For you are my hiding place;you protect me from trouble.You surround me with songs of victory. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says, “I will guide you along the best pathway for your life.I will advise you and watch over you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Do not be like a senseless horse or mulethat needs a bit and bridle to keep it under control.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Many sorrows come to the wicked,but unfailing love surrounds those who trust the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So rejoice in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and be glad, all you who obey him!Shout for joy, all you whose hearts are pure!"
		},
		"33": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Let the godly sing for joy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;it is fitting for the pure to praise him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with melodies on the lyre;make music for him on the ten-stringed harp.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Sing a new song of praise to him;play skillfully on the harp, and sing with joy.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> holds true,and we can trust everything he does.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He loves whatever is just and good;the unfailing love of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> fills the earth.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> merely spoke,and the heavens were created.He breathed the word,and all the stars were born.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He assigned the sea its boundariesand locked the oceans in vast reservoirs.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Let the whole world fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,and let everyone stand in awe of him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For when he spoke, the world began!It appeared at his command.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> frustrates the plans of the nationsand thwarts all their schemes.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s plans stand firm forever;his intentions can never be shaken.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>What joy for the nation whose God is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,whose people he has chosen as his inheritance.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> looks down from heavenand sees the whole human race.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>From his throne he observesall who live on the earth.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He made their hearts,so he understands everything they do.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The best-equipped army cannot save a king,nor is great strength enough to save a warrior.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Don’t count on your warhorse to give you victory—for all its strength, it cannot save you.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> watches over those who fear him,those who rely on his unfailing love.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He rescues them from deathand keeps them alive in times of famine.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>We put our hope in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.He is our help and our shield.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>In him our hearts rejoice,for we trust in his holy name.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Let your unfailing love surround us, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,for our hope is in you alone."
		},
		"34": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>I will praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at all times.I will constantly speak his praises.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I will boast only in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;let all who are helpless take heart.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Come, let us tell of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s greatness;let us exalt his name together.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he answered me.He freed me from all my fears.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Those who look to him for help will be radiant with joy;no shadow of shame will darken their faces.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>In my desperation I prayed, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> listened;he saved me from all my troubles.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is a guard;he surrounds and defends all who fear him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Taste and see that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is good.Oh, the joys of those who take refuge in him!",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you his godly people,for those who fear him will have all they need.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Even strong young lions sometimes go hungry,but those who trust in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will lack no good thing.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Come, my children, and listen to me,and I will teach you to fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Does anyone want to live a lifethat is long and prosperous?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then keep your tongue from speaking eviland your lips from telling lies!",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Turn away from evil and do good.Search for peace, and work to maintain it.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> watch over those who do right;his ears are open to their cries for help.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> turns his face against those who do evil;he will erase their memory from the earth.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> hears his people when they call to him for help.He rescues them from all their troubles.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is close to the brokenhearted;he rescues those whose spirits are crushed.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The righteous person faces many troubles,but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> comes to the rescue each time.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> protects the bones of the righteous;not one of them is broken!",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Calamity will surely destroy the wicked,and those who hate the righteous will be punished.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will redeem those who serve him.No one who takes refuge in him will be condemned."
		},
		"35": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, oppose those who oppose me.Fight those who fight against me.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Put on your armor, and take up your shield.Prepare for battle, and come to my aid.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Lift up your spear and javelinagainst those who pursue me.Let me hear you say,“I will give you victory!”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Bring shame and disgrace on those trying to kill me;turn them back and humiliate those who want to harm me.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Blow them away like chaff in the wind—a wind sent by the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Make their path dark and slippery,with the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> pursuing them.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I did them no wrong, but they laid a trap for me.I did them no wrong, but they dug a pit to catch me.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So let sudden ruin come upon them!Let them be caught in the trap they set for me!Let them be destroyed in the pit they dug for me.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then I will rejoice in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.I will be glad because he rescues me.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>With every bone in my body I will praise him:“<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who can compare with you?Who else rescues the helpless from the strong?Who else protects the helpless and poor from those who rob them?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Malicious witnesses testify against me.They accuse me of crimes I know nothing about.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They repay me evil for good.I am sick with despair.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Yet when they were ill, I grieved for them.I denied myself by fasting for them,but my prayers returned unanswered.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>I was sad, as though they were my friends or family,as if I were grieving for my own mother.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But they are glad now that I am in trouble;they gleefully join together against me.I am attacked by people I don’t even know;they slander me constantly.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>They mock me and call me names;they snarl at me.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>How long, O Lord, will you look on and do nothing?Rescue me from their fierce attacks.Protect my life from these lions!",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then I will thank you in front of the great assembly.I will praise you before all the people.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Don’t let my treacherous enemies rejoice over my defeat.Don’t let those who hate me without cause gloat over my sorrow.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>They don’t talk of peace;they plot against innocent people who mind their own business.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They shout, “Aha! Aha!With our own eyes we saw him do it!”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you know all about this.Do not stay silent.Do not abandon me now, O Lord.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Wake up! Rise to my defense!Take up my case, my God and my Lord.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Declare me not guilty, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, for you give justice.Don’t let my enemies laugh about me in my troubles.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Don’t let them say, “Look, we got what we wanted!Now we will eat him alive!”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>May those who rejoice at my troublesbe humiliated and disgraced.May those who triumph over mebe covered with shame and dishonor.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But give great joy to those who came to my defense.Let them continually say, “Great is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,who delights in blessing his servant with peace!”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then I will proclaim your justice,and I will praise you all day long."
		},
		"36": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Sin whispers to the wicked, deep within their hearts.They have no fear of God at all.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>In their blind conceit,they cannot see how wicked they really are.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Everything they say is crooked and deceitful.They refuse to act wisely or do good.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They lie awake at night, hatching sinful plots.Their actions are never good.They make no attempt to turn from evil.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Your unfailing love, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, is as vast as the heavens;your faithfulness reaches beyond the clouds.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Your righteousness is like the mighty mountains,your justice like the ocean depths.You care for people and animals alike, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>How precious is your unfailing love, O God!All humanity finds shelterin the shadow of your wings.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You feed them from the abundance of your own house,letting them drink from your river of delights.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For you are the fountain of life,the light by which we see.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Pour out your unfailing love on those who love you;give justice to those with honest hearts.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Don’t let the proud trample meor the wicked push me around.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Look! Those who do evil have fallen!They are thrown down, never to rise again."
		},
		"37": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Don’t worry about the wickedor envy those who do wrong.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>For like grass, they soon fade away.Like spring flowers, they soon wither.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Trust in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and do good.Then you will live safely in the land and prosper.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Take delight in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,and he will give you your heart’s desires.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Commit everything you do to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.Trust him, and he will help you.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He will make your innocence radiate like the dawn,and the justice of your cause will shine like the noonday sun.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Be still in the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,and wait patiently for him to act.Don’t worry about evil people who prosperor fret about their wicked schemes.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Stop being angry!Turn from your rage!Do not lose your temper—it only leads to harm.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For the wicked will be destroyed,but those who trust in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will possess the land.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Soon the wicked will disappear.Though you look for them, they will be gone.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The lowly will possess the landand will live in peace and prosperity.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The wicked plot against the godly;they snarl at them in defiance.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But the Lord just laughs,for he sees their day of judgment coming.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The wicked draw their swordsand string their bowsto kill the poor and the oppressed,to slaughter those who do right.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But their swords will stab their own hearts,and their bows will be broken.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>It is better to be godly and have littlethan to be evil and rich.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>For the strength of the wicked will be shattered,but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> takes care of the godly.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Day by day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> takes care of the innocent,and they will receive an inheritance that lasts forever.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They will not be disgraced in hard times;even in famine they will have more than enough.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But the wicked will die.The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s enemies are like flowers in a field—they will disappear like smoke.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The wicked borrow and never repay,but the godly are generous givers.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Those the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> blesses will possess the land,but those he curses will die.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> directs the steps of the godly.He delights in every detail of their lives.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Though they stumble, they will never fall,for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> holds them by the hand.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Once I was young, and now I am old.Yet I have never seen the godly abandonedor their children begging for bread.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The godly always give generous loans to others,and their children are a blessing.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Turn from evil and do good,and you will live in the land forever.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> loves justice,and he will never abandon the godly.He will keep them safe forever,but the children of the wicked will die.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The godly will possess the landand will live there forever.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The godly offer good counsel;they teach right from wrong.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>They have made God’s law their own,so they will never slip from his path.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The wicked wait in ambush for the godly,looking for an excuse to kill them.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will not let the wicked succeedor let the godly be condemned when they are put on trial.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Put your hope in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.Travel steadily along his path.He will honor you by giving you the land.You will see the wicked destroyed.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>I have seen wicked and ruthless peopleflourishing like a tree in its native soil.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>But when I looked again, they were gone!Though I searched for them, I could not find them!",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Look at those who are honest and good,for a wonderful future awaits those who love peace.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>But the rebellious will be destroyed;they have no future.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rescues the godly;he is their fortress in times of trouble.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> helps them,rescuing them from the wicked.He saves them,and they find shelter in him."
		},
		"38": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, don’t rebuke me in your angeror discipline me in your rage!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Your arrows have struck deep,and your blows are crushing me.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Because of your anger, my whole body is sick;my health is broken because of my sins.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>My guilt overwhelms me—it is a burden too heavy to bear.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>My wounds fester and stinkbecause of my foolish sins.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I am bent over and racked with pain.All day long I walk around filled with grief.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>A raging fever burns within me,and my health is broken.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I am exhausted and completely crushed.My groans come from an anguished heart.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You know what I long for, Lord;you hear my every sigh.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>My heart beats wildly, my strength fails,and I am going blind.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>My loved ones and friends stay away, fearing my disease.Even my own family stands at a distance.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Meanwhile, my enemies lay traps to kill me.Those who wish me harm make plans to ruin me.All day long they plan their treachery.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But I am deaf to all their threats.I am silent before them as one who cannot speak.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>I choose to hear nothing,and I make no reply.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>For I am waiting for you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.You must answer for me, O Lord my God.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>I prayed, “Don’t let my enemies gloat over meor rejoice at my downfall.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I am on the verge of collapse,facing constant pain.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But I confess my sins;I am deeply sorry for what I have done.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>I have many aggressive enemies;they hate me without reason.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>They repay me evil for goodand oppose me for pursuing good.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Do not abandon me, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.Do not stand at a distance, my God.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Come quickly to help me,O Lord my savior."
		},
		"39": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>I said to myself, “I will watch what I doand not sin in what I say.I will hold my tonguewhen the ungodly are around me.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But as I stood there in silence—not even speaking of good things—the turmoil within me grew worse.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The more I thought about it,the hotter I got,igniting a fire of words:",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, remind me how brief my time on earth will be.Remind me that my days are numbered—how fleeting my life is.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You have made my life no longer than the width of my hand.My entire lifetime is just a moment to you;at best, each of us is but a breath.” <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>We are merely moving shadows,and all our busy rushing ends in nothing.We heap up wealth,not knowing who will spend it.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And so, Lord, where do I put my hope?My only hope is in you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Rescue me from my rebellion.Do not let fools mock me.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>I am silent before you; I won’t say a word,for my punishment is from you.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But please stop striking me!I am exhausted by the blows from your hand.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When you discipline us for our sins,you consume like a moth what is precious to us.Each of us is but a breath. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Hear my prayer, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!Listen to my cries for help!Don’t ignore my tears.For I am your guest—a traveler passing through,as my ancestors were before me.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Leave me alone so I can smile againbefore I am gone and exist no more."
		},
		"40": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>I waited patiently for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to help me,and he turned to me and heard my cry.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He lifted me out of the pit of despair,out of the mud and the mire.He set my feet on solid groundand steadied me as I walked along.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He has given me a new song to sing,a hymn of praise to our God.Many will see what he has done and be amazed.They will put their trust in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Oh, the joys of those who trust the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,who have no confidence in the proudor in those who worship idols.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, you have performed many wonders for us.Your plans for us are too numerous to list.You have no equal.If I tried to recite all your wonderful deeds,I would never come to the end of them.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You take no delight in sacrifices or offerings.Now that you have made me listen, I finally understand—you don’t require burnt offerings or sin offerings.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then I said, “Look, I have come.As is written about me in the Scriptures:",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I take joy in doing your will, my God,for your instructions are written on my heart.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>I have told all your people about your justice.I have not been afraid to speak out,as you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, well know.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>I have not kept the good news of your justice hidden in my heart;I have talked about your faithfulness and saving power.I have told everyone in the great assemblyof your unfailing love and faithfulness.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, don’t hold back your tender mercies from me.Let your unfailing love and faithfulness always protect me.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For troubles surround me—too many to count!My sins pile up so highI can’t see my way out.They outnumber the hairs on my head.I have lost all courage.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Please, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, rescue me!Come quickly, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and help me.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>May those who try to destroy mebe humiliated and put to shame.May those who take delight in my troublebe turned back in disgrace.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Let them be horrified by their shame,for they said, “Aha! We’ve got him now!”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But may all who search for yoube filled with joy and gladness in you.May those who love your salvationrepeatedly shout, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is great!”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>As for me, since I am poor and needy,let the Lord keep me in his thoughts.You are my helper and my savior.O my God, do not delay."
		},
		"41": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Oh, the joys of those who are kind to the poor!The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rescues them when they are in trouble.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> protects themand keeps them alive.He gives them prosperity in the landand rescues them from their enemies.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> nurses them when they are sickand restores them to health.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,” I prayed, “have mercy on me.Heal me, for I have sinned against you.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But my enemies say nothing but evil about me.“How soon will he die and be forgotten?” they ask.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They visit me as if they were my friends,but all the while they gather gossip,and when they leave, they spread it everywhere.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>All who hate me whisper about me,imagining the worst.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“He has some fatal disease,” they say.“He will never get out of that bed!”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Even my best friend, the one I trusted completely,the one who shared my food, has turned against me.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, have mercy on me.Make me well again, so I can pay them back!",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>I know you are pleased with me,for you have not let my enemies triumph over me.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>You have preserved my life because I am innocent;you have brought me into your presence forever.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel,who lives from everlasting to everlasting.Amen and amen!"
		},
		"42": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>As the deer longs for streams of water,so I long for you, O God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I thirst for God, the living God.When can I go and stand before him?",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Day and night I have only tears for food,while my enemies continually taunt me, saying,“Where is this God of yours?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>My heart is breakingas I remember how it used to be:I walked among the crowds of worshipers,leading a great procession to the house of God,singing for joy and giving thanksamid the sound of a great celebration!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Why am I discouraged?Why is my heart so sad?I will put my hope in God!I will praise him again—my Savior and",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum mid-line\">6 </sup>my God! Now I am deeply discouraged,but I will remember you—even from distant Mount Hermon, the source of the Jordan,from the land of Mount Mizar.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I hear the tumult of the raging seasas your waves and surging tides sweep over me.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But each day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> pours his unfailing love upon me,and through each night I sing his songs,praying to God who gives me life.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“O God my rock,” I cry,“Why have you forgotten me?Why must I wander around in grief,oppressed by my enemies?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Their taunts break my bones.They scoff, “Where is this God of yours?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Why am I discouraged?Why is my heart so sad?I will put my hope in God!I will praise him again—my Savior and my God!"
		},
		"43": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Declare me innocent, O God!Defend me against these ungodly people.Rescue me from these unjust liars.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>For you are God, my only safe haven.Why have you tossed me aside?Why must I wander around in grief,oppressed by my enemies?",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Send out your light and your truth;let them guide me.Let them lead me to your holy mountain,to the place where you live.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>There I will go to the altar of God,to God—the source of all my joy.I will praise you with my harp,O God, my God!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Why am I discouraged?Why is my heart so sad?I will put my hope in God!I will praise him again—my Savior and my God!"
		},
		"44": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O God, we have heard it with our own ears—our ancestors have told usof all you did in their day,in days long ago:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>You drove out the pagan nations by your powerand gave all the land to our ancestors.You crushed their enemiesand set our ancestors free.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They did not conquer the land with their swords;it was not their own strong arm that gave them victory.It was your right hand and strong armand the blinding light from your face that helped them,for you loved them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You are my King and my God.You command victories for Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Only by your power can we push back our enemies;only in your name can we trample our foes.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I do not trust in my bow;I do not count on my sword to save me.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>You are the one who gives us victory over our enemies;you disgrace those who hate us.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>O God, we give glory to you all day longand constantly praise your name. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But now you have tossed us aside in dishonor.You no longer lead our armies to battle.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You make us retreat from our enemiesand allow those who hate us to plunder our land.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You have butchered us like sheepand scattered us among the nations.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>You sold your precious people for a pittance,making nothing on the sale.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>You let our neighbors mock us.We are an object of scorn and derision to those around us.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You have made us the butt of their jokes;they shake their heads at us in scorn.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>We can’t escape the constant humiliation;shame is written across our faces.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>All we hear are the taunts of our mockers.All we see are our vengeful enemies.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>All this has happened though we have not forgotten you.We have not violated your covenant.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Our hearts have not deserted you.We have not strayed from your path.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Yet you have crushed us in the jackal’s desert home.You have covered us with darkness and death.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>If we had forgotten the name of our Godor spread our hands in prayer to foreign gods,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>God would surely have known it,for he knows the secrets of every heart.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But for your sake we are killed every day;we are being slaughtered like sheep.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Wake up, O Lord! Why do you sleep?Get up! Do not reject us forever.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Why do you look the other way?Why do you ignore our suffering and oppression?",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>We collapse in the dust,lying face down in the dirt.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Rise up! Help us!Ransom us because of your unfailing love."
		},
		"45": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Beautiful words stir my heart.I will recite a lovely poem about the king,for my tongue is like the pen of a skillful poet.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>You are the most handsome of all.Gracious words stream from your lips.God himself has blessed you forever.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Put on your sword, O mighty warrior!You are so glorious, so majestic!",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>In your majesty, ride out to victory,defending truth, humility, and justice.Go forth to perform awe-inspiring deeds!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Your arrows are sharp, piercing your enemies’ hearts.The nations fall beneath your feet.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Your throne, O God, endures forever and ever.You rule with a scepter of justice.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>You love justice and hate evil.Therefore God, your God, has anointed you,pouring out the oil of joy on you more than on anyone else.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Myrrh, aloes, and cassia perfume your robes.In ivory palaces the music of strings entertains you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Kings’ daughters are among your noble women.At your right side stands the queen,wearing jewelry of finest gold from Ophir!",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Listen to me, O royal daughter; take to heart what I say.Forget your people and your family far away.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>For your royal husband delights in your beauty;honor him, for he is your lord.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The princess of Tyre will shower you with gifts.The wealthy will beg your favor.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The bride, a princess, looks gloriousin her golden gown.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>In her beautiful robes, she is led to the king,accompanied by her bridesmaids.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>What a joyful and enthusiastic processionas they enter the king’s palace!",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Your sons will become kings like their father.You will make them rulers over many lands.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I will bring honor to your name in every generation.Therefore, the nations will praise you forever and ever."
		},
		"46": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>God is our refuge and strength,always ready to help in times of trouble.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So we will not fear when earthquakes comeand the mountains crumble into the sea.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Let the oceans roar and foam.Let the mountains tremble as the waters surge! <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>A river brings joy to the city of our God,the sacred home of the Most High.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>God dwells in that city; it cannot be destroyed.From the very break of day, God will protect it.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The nations are in chaos,and their kingdoms crumble!God’s voice thunders,and the earth melts!",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of Heaven’s Armies is here among us;the God of Israel is our fortress. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Come, see the glorious works of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>:See how he brings destruction upon the world.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He causes wars to end throughout the earth.He breaks the bow and snaps the spear;he burns the shields with fire.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Be still, and know that I am God!I will be honored by every nation.I will be honored throughout the world.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of Heaven’s Armies is here among us;the God of Israel is our fortress. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>"
		},
		"47": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Come, everyone! Clap your hands!Shout to God with joyful praise!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Most High is awesome.He is the great King of all the earth.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He subdues the nations before us,putting our enemies beneath our feet.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He chose the Promised Land as our inheritance,the proud possession of Jacob’s descendants, whom he loves. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>God has ascended with a mighty shout.The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has ascended with trumpets blaring.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Sing praises to God, sing praises;sing praises to our King, sing praises!",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For God is the King over all the earth.Praise him with a psalm.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>God reigns above the nations,sitting on his holy throne.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The rulers of the world have gathered togetherwith the people of the God of Abraham.For all the kings of the earth belong to God.He is highly honored everywhere."
		},
		"48": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>How great is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,how deserving of praise,in the city of our God,which sits on his holy mountain!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>It is high and magnificent;the whole earth rejoices to see it!Mount Zion, the holy mountain,is the city of the great King!",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>God himself is in Jerusalem’s towers,revealing himself as its defender.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The kings of the earth joined forcesand advanced against the city.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But when they saw it, they were stunned;they were terrified and ran away.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They were gripped with terrorand writhed in pain like a woman in labor.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>You destroyed them like the mighty ships of Tarshishshattered by a powerful east wind.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>We had heard of the city’s glory,but now we have seen it ourselves—the city of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of Heaven’s Armies.It is the city of our God;he will make it safe forever. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>O God, we meditate on your unfailing loveas we worship in your Temple.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>As your name deserves, O God,you will be praised to the ends of the earth.Your strong right hand is filled with victory.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Let the people on Mount Zion rejoice.Let all the towns of Judah be gladbecause of your justice.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Go, inspect the city of Jerusalem.Walk around and count the many towers.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Take note of the fortified walls,and tour all the citadels,that you may describe themto future generations.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>For that is what God is like.He is our God forever and ever,and he will guide us until we die."
		},
		"49": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Listen to this, all you people!Pay attention, everyone in the world!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>High and low,rich and poor—listen!",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For my words are wise,and my thoughts are filled with insight.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I listen carefully to many proverbsand solve riddles with inspiration from a harp.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Why should I fear when trouble comes,when enemies surround me?",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They trust in their wealthand boast of great riches.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Yet they cannot redeem themselves from deathby paying a ransom to God.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Redemption does not come so easily,for no one can ever pay enough",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>to live foreverand never see the grave.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Those who are wise must finally die,just like the foolish and senseless,leaving all their wealth behind.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The grave is their eternal home,where they will stay forever.They may name their estates after themselves,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>but their fame will not last.They will die, just like animals.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>This is the fate of fools,though they are remembered as being wise. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Like sheep, they are led to the grave,where death will be their shepherd.In the morning the godly will rule over them.Their bodies will rot in the grave,far from their grand estates.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But as for me, God will redeem my life.He will snatch me from the power of the grave. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So don’t be dismayed when the wicked grow richand their homes become ever more splendid.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>For when they die, they take nothing with them.Their wealth will not follow them into the grave.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>In this life they consider themselves fortunateand are applauded for their success.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But they will die like all before themand never again see the light of day.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>People who boast of their wealth don’t understand;they will die, just like animals."
		},
		"50": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the Mighty One, is God,and he has spoken;he has summoned all humanityfrom where the sun rises to where it sets.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>From Mount Zion, the perfection of beauty,God shines in glorious radiance.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Our God approaches,and he is not silent.Fire devours everything in his way,and a great storm rages around him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He calls on the heavens above and earth belowto witness the judgment of his people.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Bring my faithful people to me—those who made a covenant with me by giving sacrifices.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then let the heavens proclaim his justice,for God himself will be the judge. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“O my people, listen as I speak.Here are my charges against you, O Israel:I am God, your God!",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I have no complaint about your sacrificesor the burnt offerings you constantly offer.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But I do not need the bulls from your barnsor the goats from your pens.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For all the animals of the forest are mine,and I own the cattle on a thousand hills.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>I know every bird on the mountains,and all the animals of the field are mine.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>If I were hungry, I would not tell you,for all the world is mine and everything in it.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Do I eat the meat of bulls?Do I drink the blood of goats?",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Make thankfulness your sacrifice to God,and keep the vows you made to the Most High.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then call on me when you are in trouble,and I will rescue you,and you will give me glory.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But God says to the wicked:“Why bother reciting my decreesand pretending to obey my covenant?",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>For you refuse my disciplineand treat my words like trash.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When you see thieves, you approve of them,and you spend your time with adulterers.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Your mouth is filled with wickedness,and your tongue is full of lies.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You sit around and slander your brother—your own mother’s son.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>While you did all this, I remained silent,and you thought I didn’t care.But now I will rebuke you,listing all my charges against you.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Repent, all of you who forget me,or I will tear you apart,and no one will help you.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But giving thanks is a sacrifice that truly honors me.If you keep to my path,I will reveal to you the salvation of God.”"
		},
		"51": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Have mercy on me, O God,because of your unfailing love.Because of your great compassion,blot out the stain of my sins.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Wash me clean from my guilt.Purify me from my sin.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For I recognize my rebellion;it haunts me day and night.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Against you, and you alone, have I sinned;I have done what is evil in your sight.You will be proved right in what you say,and your judgment against me is just.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For I was born a sinner—yes, from the moment my mother conceived me.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But you desire honesty from the womb,teaching me wisdom even there.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Purify me from my sins, and I will be clean;wash me, and I will be whiter than snow.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Oh, give me back my joy again;you have broken me—now let me rejoice.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Don’t keep looking at my sins.Remove the stain of my guilt.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Create in me a clean heart, O God.Renew a loyal spirit within me.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Do not banish me from your presence,and don’t take your Holy Spirit from me.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Restore to me the joy of your salvation,and make me willing to obey you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then I will teach your ways to rebels,and they will return to you.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Forgive me for shedding blood, O God who saves;then I will joyfully sing of your forgiveness.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Unseal my lips, O Lord,that my mouth may praise you.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>You do not desire a sacrifice, or I would offer one.You do not want a burnt offering.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The sacrifice you desire is a broken spirit.You will not reject a broken and repentant heart, O God.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Look with favor on Zion and help her;rebuild the walls of Jerusalem.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then you will be pleased with sacrifices offered in the right spirit—with burnt offerings and whole burnt offerings.Then bulls will again be sacrificed on your altar."
		},
		"52": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Why do you boast about your crimes, great warrior?Don’t you realize God’s justice continues forever?",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>All day long you plot destruction.Your tongue cuts like a sharp razor;you’re an expert at telling lies.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You love evil more than goodand lies more than truth. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You love to destroy others with your words,you liar!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But God will strike you down once and for all.He will pull you from your homeand uproot you from the land of the living. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The righteous will see it and be amazed.They will laugh and say,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Look what happens to mighty warriorswho do not trust in God.They trust their wealth insteadand grow more and more bold in their wickedness.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But I am like an olive tree, thriving in the house of God.I will always trust in God’s unfailing love.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>I will praise you forever, O God,for what you have done.I will trust in your good namein the presence of your faithful people."
		},
		"53": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Only fools say in their hearts,“There is no God.”They are corrupt, and their actions are evil;not one of them does good!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>God looks down from heavenon the entire human race;he looks to see if anyone is truly wise,if anyone seeks God.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But no, all have turned away;all have become corrupt.No one does good,not a single one!",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Will those who do evil never learn?They eat up my people like breadand wouldn’t think of praying to God.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Terror will grip them,terror like they have never known before.God will scatter the bones of your enemies.You will put them to shame, for God has rejected them.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Who will come from Mount Zion to rescue Israel?When God restores his people,Jacob will shout with joy, and Israel will rejoice."
		},
		"54": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Come with great power, O God, and rescue me!Defend me with your might.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Listen to my prayer, O God.Pay attention to my plea.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For strangers are attacking me;violent people are trying to kill me.They care nothing for God. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But God is my helper.The Lord keeps me alive!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>May the evil plans of my enemies be turned against them.Do as you promised and put an end to them.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I will sacrifice a voluntary offering to you;I will praise your name, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,for it is good.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For you have rescued me from my troublesand helped me to triumph over my enemies."
		},
		"55": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Listen to my prayer, O God.Do not ignore my cry for help!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Please listen and answer me,for I am overwhelmed by my troubles.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>My enemies shout at me,making loud and wicked threats.They bring trouble on meand angrily hunt me down.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>My heart pounds in my chest.The terror of death assaults me.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Fear and trembling overwhelm me,and I can’t stop shaking.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Oh, that I had wings like a dove;then I would fly away and rest!",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I would fly far awayto the quiet of the wilderness. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>How quickly I would escape—far from this wild storm of hatred.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Confuse them, Lord, and frustrate their plans,for I see violence and conflict in the city.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Its walls are patrolled day and night against invaders,but the real danger is wickedness within the city.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Everything is falling apart;threats and cheating are rampant in the streets.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>It is not an enemy who taunts me—I could bear that.It is not my foes who so arrogantly insult me—I could have hidden from them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Instead, it is you—my equal,my companion and close friend.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>What good fellowship we once enjoyedas we walked together to the house of God.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Let death stalk my enemies;let the grave swallow them alive,for evil makes its home within them.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But I will call on God,and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will rescue me.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Morning, noon, and nightI cry out in my distress,and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> hears my voice.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He ransoms me and keeps me safefrom the battle waged against me,though many still oppose me.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>God, who has ruled forever,will hear me and humble them. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>For my enemies refuse to change their ways;they do not fear God.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>As for my companion, he betrayed his friends;he broke his promises.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>His words are as smooth as butter,but in his heart is war.His words are as soothing as lotion,but underneath are daggers!",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Give your burdens to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,and he will take care of you.He will not permit the godly to slip and fall.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But you, O God, will send the wickeddown to the pit of destruction.Murderers and liars will die young,but I am trusting you to save me."
		},
		"56": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O God, have mercy on me,for people are hounding me.My foes attack me all day long.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I am constantly hounded by those who slander me,and many are boldly attacking me.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But when I am afraid,I will put my trust in you.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I praise God for what he has promised.I trust in God, so why should I be afraid?What can mere mortals do to me?",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They are always twisting what I say;they spend their days plotting to harm me.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They come together to spy on me—watching my every step, eager to kill me.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Don’t let them get away with their wickedness;in your anger, O God, bring them down.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You keep track of all my sorrows.You have collected all my tears in your bottle.You have recorded each one in your book.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>My enemies will retreat when I call to you for help.This I know: God is on my side!",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>I praise God for what he has promised;yes, I praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for what he has promised.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>I trust in God, so why should I be afraid?What can mere mortals do to me?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>I will fulfill my vows to you, O God,and will offer a sacrifice of thanks for your help.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>For you have rescued me from death;you have kept my feet from slipping.So now I can walk in your presence, O God,in your life-giving light."
		},
		"57": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Have mercy on me, O God, have mercy!I look to you for protection.I will hide beneath the shadow of your wingsuntil the danger passes by.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I cry out to God Most High,to God who will fulfill his purpose for me.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He will send help from heaven to rescue me,disgracing those who hound me. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>My God will send forth his unfailing love and faithfulness.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I am surrounded by fierce lionswho greedily devour human prey—whose teeth pierce like spears and arrows,and whose tongues cut like swords.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Be exalted, O God, above the highest heavens!May your glory shine over all the earth.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>My enemies have set a trap for me.I am weary from distress.They have dug a deep pit in my path,but they themselves have fallen into it. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>My heart is confident in you, O God;my heart is confident.No wonder I can sing your praises!",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Wake up, my heart!Wake up, O lyre and harp!I will wake the dawn with my song.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>I will thank you, Lord, among all the people.I will sing your praises among the nations.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For your unfailing love is as high as the heavens.Your faithfulness reaches to the clouds.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Be exalted, O God, above the highest heavens.May your glory shine over all the earth."
		},
		"58": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Justice—do you rulers know the meaning of the word?Do you judge the people fairly?",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>No! You plot injustice in your hearts.You spread violence throughout the land.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>These wicked people are born sinners;even from birth they have lied and gone their own way.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They spit venom like deadly snakes;they are like cobras that refuse to listen,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>ignoring the tunes of the snake charmers,no matter how skillfully they play.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Break off their fangs, O God!Smash the jaws of these lions, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>May they disappear like water into thirsty ground.Make their weapons useless in their hands.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>May they be like snails that dissolve into slime,like a stillborn child who will never see the sun.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>God will sweep them away, both young and old,faster than a pot heats over burning thorns.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The godly will rejoice when they see injustice avenged.They will wash their feet in the blood of the wicked.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then at last everyone will say,“There truly is a reward for those who live for God;surely there is a God who judges justly here on earth.”"
		},
		"59": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Rescue me from my enemies, O God.Protect me from those who have come to destroy me.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Rescue me from these criminals;save me from these murderers.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They have set an ambush for me.Fierce enemies are out there waiting, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,though I have not sinned or offended them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I have done nothing wrong,yet they prepare to attack me.Wake up! See what is happening and help me!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Heaven’s Armies, the God of Israel,wake up and punish those hostile nations.Show no mercy to wicked traitors. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They come out at night,snarling like vicious dogsas they prowl the streets.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Listen to the filth that comes from their mouths;their words cut like swords.“After all, who can hear us?” they sneer.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you laugh at them.You scoff at all the hostile nations.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You are my strength; I wait for you to rescue me,for you, O God, are my fortress.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>In his unfailing love, my God will stand with me.He will let me look down in triumph on all my enemies.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Don’t kill them, for my people soon forget such lessons;stagger them with your power, and bring them to their knees,O Lord our shield.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Because of the sinful things they say,because of the evil that is on their lips,let them be captured by their pride,their curses, and their lies.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Destroy them in your anger!Wipe them out completely!Then the whole world will knowthat God reigns in Israel. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>My enemies come out at night,snarling like vicious dogsas they prowl the streets.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>They scavenge for foodbut go to sleep unsatisfied.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But as for me, I will sing about your power.Each morning I will sing with joy about your unfailing love.For you have been my refuge,a place of safety when I am in distress.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>O my Strength, to you I sing praises,for you, O God, are my refuge,the God who shows me unfailing love."
		},
		"60": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>You have rejected us, O God, and broken our defenses.You have been angry with us; now restore us to your favor.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>You have shaken our land and split it open.Seal the cracks, for the land trembles.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You have been very hard on us,making us drink wine that sent us reeling.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But you have raised a banner for those who fear you—a rallying point in the face of attack. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now rescue your beloved people.Answer and save us by your power.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>God has promised this by his holiness:“I will divide up Shechem with joy.I will measure out the valley of Succoth.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Gilead is mine,and Manasseh, too.Ephraim, my helmet, will produce my warriors,and Judah, my scepter, will produce my kings.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But Moab, my washbasin, will become my servant,and I will wipe my feet on Edomand shout in triumph over Philistia.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Who will bring me into the fortified city?Who will bring me victory over Edom?",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Have you rejected us, O God?Will you no longer march with our armies?",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Oh, please help us against our enemies,for all human help is useless.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>With God’s help we will do mighty things,for he will trample down our foes."
		},
		"61": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O God, listen to my cry!Hear my prayer!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>From the ends of the earth,I cry to you for helpwhen my heart is overwhelmed.Lead me to the towering rock of safety,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>for you are my safe refuge,a fortress where my enemies cannot reach me.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Let me live forever in your sanctuary,safe beneath the shelter of your wings! <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For you have heard my vows, O God.You have given me an inheritance reserved for those who fear your name.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Add many years to the life of the king!May his years span the generations!",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>May he reign under God’s protection forever.May your unfailing love and faithfulness watch over him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then I will sing praises to your name foreveras I fulfill my vows each day."
		},
		"62": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>I wait quietly before God,for my victory comes from him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He alone is my rock and my salvation,my fortress where I will never be shaken.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So many enemies against one man—all of them trying to kill me.To them I’m just a broken-down wallor a tottering fence.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They plan to topple me from my high position.They delight in telling lies about me.They praise me to my facebut curse me in their hearts. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Let all that I am wait quietly before God,for my hope is in him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He alone is my rock and my salvation,my fortress where I will not be shaken.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>My victory and honor come from God alone.He is my refuge, a rock where no enemy can reach me.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>O my people, trust in him at all times.Pour out your heart to him,for God is our refuge. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Common people are as worthless as a puff of wind,and the powerful are not what they appear to be.If you weigh them on the scales,together they are lighter than a breath of air.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Don’t make your living by extortionor put your hope in stealing.And if your wealth increases,don’t make it the center of your life.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>God has spoken plainly,and I have heard it many times:Power, O God, belongs to you;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>unfailing love, O Lord, is yours.Surely you repay all peopleaccording to what they have done."
		},
		"63": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O God, you are my God;I earnestly search for you.My soul thirsts for you;my whole body longs for youin this parched and weary landwhere there is no water.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I have seen you in your sanctuaryand gazed upon your power and glory.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Your unfailing love is better than life itself;how I praise you!",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I will praise you as long as I live,lifting up my hands to you in prayer.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You satisfy me more than the richest feast.I will praise you with songs of joy.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I lie awake thinking of you,meditating on you through the night.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Because you are my helper,I sing for joy in the shadow of your wings.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I cling to you;your strong right hand holds me securely.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But those plotting to destroy me will come to ruin.They will go down into the depths of the earth.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They will die by the swordand become the food of jackals.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But the king will rejoice in God.All who swear to tell the truth will praise him,while liars will be silenced."
		},
		"64": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O God, listen to my complaint.Protect my life from my enemies’ threats.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Hide me from the plots of this evil mob,from this gang of wrongdoers.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They sharpen their tongues like swordsand aim their bitter words like arrows.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They shoot from ambush at the innocent,attacking suddenly and fearlessly.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They encourage each other to do eviland plan how to set their traps in secret.“Who will ever notice?” they ask.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>As they plot their crimes, they say,“We have devised the perfect plan!”Yes, the human heart and mind are cunning.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But God himself will shoot them with his arrows,suddenly striking them down.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Their own tongues will ruin them,and all who see them will shake their heads in scorn.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then everyone will be afraid;they will proclaim the mighty acts of Godand realize all the amazing things he does.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The godly will rejoice in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>and find shelter in him.And those who do what is rightwill praise him."
		},
		"65": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>What mighty praise, O God,belongs to you in Zion.We will fulfill our vows to you,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>for you answer our prayers.All of us must come to you.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Though we are overwhelmed by our sins,you forgive them all.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>What joy for those you choose to bring near,those who live in your holy courts.What festivities await usinside your holy Temple.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You faithfully answer our prayers with awesome deeds,O God our savior.You are the hope of everyone on earth,even those who sail on distant seas.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You formed the mountains by your powerand armed yourself with mighty strength.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>You quieted the raging oceanswith their pounding wavesand silenced the shouting of the nations.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Those who live at the ends of the earthstand in awe of your wonders.From where the sun rises to where it sets,you inspire shouts of joy.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You take care of the earth and water it,making it rich and fertile.The river of God has plenty of water;it provides a bountiful harvest of grain,for you have ordered it so.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You drench the plowed ground with rain,melting the clods and leveling the ridges.You soften the earth with showersand bless its abundant crops.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You crown the year with a bountiful harvest;even the hard pathways overflow with abundance.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The grasslands of the wilderness become a lush pasture,and the hillsides blossom with joy.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The meadows are clothed with flocks of sheep,and the valleys are carpeted with grain.They all shout and sing for joy!"
		},
		"66": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Shout joyful praises to God, all the earth!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Sing about the glory of his name!Tell the world how glorious he is.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Say to God, “How awesome are your deeds!Your enemies cringe before your mighty power.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Everything on earth will worship you;they will sing your praises,shouting your name in glorious songs.” <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Come and see what our God has done,what awesome miracles he performs for people!",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He made a dry path through the Red Sea,and his people went across on foot.There we rejoiced in him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For by his great power he rules forever.He watches every movement of the nations;let no rebel rise in defiance. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Let the whole world bless our Godand loudly sing his praises.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Our lives are in his hands,and he keeps our feet from stumbling.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You have tested us, O God;you have purified us like silver.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You captured us in your netand laid the burden of slavery on our backs.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then you put a leader over us.We went through fire and flood,but you brought us to a place of great abundance.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now I come to your Temple with burnt offeringsto fulfill the vows I made to you—",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>yes, the sacred vows that I madewhen I was in deep trouble.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>That is why I am sacrificing burnt offerings to you—the best of my rams as a pleasing aroma,and a sacrifice of bulls and male goats. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Come and listen, all you who fear God,and I will tell you what he did for me.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>For I cried out to him for help,praising him as I spoke.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>If I had not confessed the sin in my heart,the Lord would not have listened.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But God did listen!He paid attention to my prayer.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Praise God, who did not ignore my prayeror withdraw his unfailing love from me."
		},
		"67": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>May God be merciful and bless us.May his face smile with favor on us. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>May your ways be known throughout the earth,your saving power among people everywhere.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>May the nations praise you, O God.Yes, may all the nations praise you.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Let the whole world sing for joy,because you govern the nations with justiceand guide the people of the whole world. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>May the nations praise you, O God.Yes, may all the nations praise you.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then the earth will yield its harvests,and God, our God, will richly bless us.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Yes, God will bless us,and people all over the world will fear him."
		},
		"68": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Rise up, O God, and scatter your enemies.Let those who hate God run for their lives.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Blow them away like smoke.Melt them like wax in a fire.Let the wicked perish in the presence of God.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But let the godly rejoice.Let them be glad in God’s presence.Let them be filled with joy.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Sing praises to God and to his name!Sing loud praises to him who rides the clouds.His name is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—rejoice in his presence!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Father to the fatherless, defender of widows—this is God, whose dwelling is holy.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>God places the lonely in families;he sets the prisoners free and gives them joy.But he makes the rebellious live in a sun-scorched land.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>O God, when you led your people out from Egypt,when you marched through the dry wasteland, <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>the earth trembled, and the heavens poured down rainbefore you, the God of Sinai,before God, the God of Israel.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You sent abundant rain, O God,to refresh the weary land.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>There your people finally settled,and with a bountiful harvest, O God,you provided for your needy people.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The Lord gives the word,and a great army brings the good news.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Enemy kings and their armies flee,while the women of Israel divide the plunder.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Even those who lived among the sheepfolds found treasures—doves with wings of silverand feathers of gold.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The Almighty scattered the enemy kingslike a blowing snowstorm on Mount Zalmon.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The mountains of Bashan are majestic,with many peaks stretching high into the sky.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Why do you look with envy, O rugged mountains,at Mount Zion, where God has chosen to live,where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> himself will live forever?",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Surrounded by unnumbered thousands of chariots,the Lord came from Mount Sinai into his sanctuary.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When you ascended to the heights,you led a crowd of captives.You received gifts from the people,even from those who rebelled against you.Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God will live among us there.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Praise the Lord; praise God our savior!For each day he carries us in his arms. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Our God is a God who saves!The Sovereign <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rescues us from death.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But God will smash the heads of his enemies,crushing the skulls of those who love their guilty ways.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The Lord says, “I will bring my enemies down from Bashan;I will bring them up from the depths of the sea.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>You, my people, will wash your feet in their blood,and even your dogs will get their share!”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Your procession has come into view, O God—the procession of my God and King as he goes into the sanctuary.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Singers are in front, musicians behind;between them are young women playing tambourines.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Praise God, all you people of Israel;praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the source of Israel’s life.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Look, the little tribe of Benjamin leads the way.Then comes a great throng of rulers from Judahand all the rulers of Zebulun and Naphtali.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Summon your might, O God.Display your power, O God, as you have in the past.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The kings of the earth are bringing tributeto your Temple in Jerusalem.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Rebuke these enemy nations—these wild animals lurking in the reeds,this herd of bulls among the weaker calves.Make them bring bars of silver in humble tribute.Scatter the nations that delight in war.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Let Egypt come with gifts of precious metals;let Ethiopia bring tribute to God.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Sing to God, you kingdoms of the earth.Sing praises to the Lord. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Sing to the one who rides across the ancient heavens,his mighty voice thundering from the sky.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Tell everyone about God’s power.His majesty shines down on Israel;his strength is mighty in the heavens.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>God is awesome in his sanctuary.The God of Israel gives power and strength to his people.Praise be to God!"
		},
		"69": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Save me, O God,for the floodwaters are up to my neck.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Deeper and deeper I sink into the mire;I can’t find a foothold.I am in deep water,and the floods overwhelm me.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I am exhausted from crying for help;my throat is parched.My eyes are swollen with weeping,waiting for my God to help me.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Those who hate me without causeoutnumber the hairs on my head.Many enemies try to destroy me with lies,demanding that I give back what I didn’t steal.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>O God, you know how foolish I am;my sins cannot be hidden from you.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Don’t let those who trust in you be ashamed because of me,O Sovereign <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of Heaven’s Armies.Don’t let me cause them to be humiliated,O God of Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For I endure insults for your sake;humiliation is written all over my face.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Even my own brothers pretend they don’t know me;they treat me like a stranger.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Passion for your house has consumed me,and the insults of those who insult you have fallen on me.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When I weep and fast,they scoff at me.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When I dress in burlap to show sorrow,they make fun of me.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>I am the favorite topic of town gossip,and all the drunks sing about me.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But I keep praying to you, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,hoping this time you will show me favor.In your unfailing love, O God,answer my prayer with your sure salvation.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Rescue me from the mud;don’t let me sink any deeper!Save me from those who hate me,and pull me from these deep waters.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Don’t let the floods overwhelm me,or the deep waters swallow me,or the pit of death devour me.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Answer my prayers, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,for your unfailing love is wonderful.Take care of me,for your mercy is so plentiful.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Don’t hide from your servant;answer me quickly, for I am in deep trouble!",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Come and redeem me;free me from my enemies.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>You know of my shame, scorn, and disgrace.You see all that my enemies are doing.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Their insults have broken my heart,and I am in despair.If only one person would show some pity;if only one would turn and comfort me.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But instead, they give me poison for food;they offer me sour wine for my thirst.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Let the bountiful table set before them become a snareand their prosperity become a trap.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Let their eyes go blind so they cannot see,and make their bodies shake continually.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Pour out your fury on them;consume them with your burning anger.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Let their homes become desolateand their tents be deserted.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>To the one you have punished, they add insult to injury;they add to the pain of those you have hurt.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Pile their sins up high,and don’t let them go free.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Erase their names from the Book of Life;don’t let them be counted among the righteous.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>I am suffering and in pain.Rescue me, O God, by your saving power.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then I will praise God’s name with singing,and I will honor him with thanksgiving.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>For this will please the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> more than sacrificing cattle,more than presenting a bull with its horns and hooves.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The humble will see their God at work and be glad.Let all who seek God’s help be encouraged.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> hears the cries of the needy;he does not despise his imprisoned people.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Praise him, O heaven and earth,the seas and all that move in them.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>For God will save Jerusalemand rebuild the towns of Judah.His people will live thereand settle in their own land.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>The descendants of those who obey him will inherit the land,and those who love him will live there in safety."
		},
		"70": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Please, God, rescue me!Come quickly, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and help me.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>May those who try to kill mebe humiliated and put to shame.May those who take delight in my troublebe turned back in disgrace.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Let them be horrified by their shame,for they said, “Aha! We’ve got him now!”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But may all who search for yoube filled with joy and gladness in you.May those who love your salvationrepeatedly shout, “God is great!”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But as for me, I am poor and needy;please hurry to my aid, O God.You are my helper and my savior;O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, do not delay."
		},
		"71": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, I have come to you for protection;don’t let me be disgraced.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Save me and rescue me,for you do what is right.Turn your ear to listen to me,and set me free.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Be my rock of safetywhere I can always hide.Give the order to save me,for you are my rock and my fortress.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>My God, rescue me from the power of the wicked,from the clutches of cruel oppressors.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>O Lord, you alone are my hope.I’ve trusted you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, from childhood.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Yes, you have been with me from birth;from my mother’s womb you have cared for me.No wonder I am always praising you!",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>My life is an example to many,because you have been my strength and protection.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>That is why I can never stop praising you;I declare your glory all day long.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And now, in my old age, don’t set me aside.Don’t abandon me when my strength is failing.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For my enemies are whispering against me.They are plotting together to kill me.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They say, “God has abandoned him.Let’s go and get him,for no one will help him now.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>O God, don’t stay away.My God, please hurry to help me.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Bring disgrace and destruction on my accusers.Humiliate and shame those who want to harm me.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But I will keep on hoping for your help;I will praise you more and more.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>I will tell everyone about your righteousness.All day long I will proclaim your saving power,though I am not skilled with words.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>I will praise your mighty deeds, O Sovereign <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.I will tell everyone that you alone are just.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>O God, you have taught me from my earliest childhood,and I constantly tell others about the wonderful things you do.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now that I am old and gray,do not abandon me, O God.Let me proclaim your power to this new generation,your mighty miracles to all who come after me.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Your righteousness, O God, reaches to the highest heavens.You have done such wonderful things.Who can compare with you, O God?",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You have allowed me to suffer much hardship,but you will restore me to life againand lift me up from the depths of the earth.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>You will restore me to even greater honorand comfort me once again.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then I will praise you with music on the harp,because you are faithful to your promises, O my God.I will sing praises to you with a lyre,O Holy One of Israel.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>I will shout for joy and sing your praises,for you have ransomed me.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>I will tell about your righteous deedsall day long,for everyone who tried to hurt mehas been shamed and humiliated."
		},
		"72": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Give your love of justice to the king, O God,and righteousness to the king’s son.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Help him judge your people in the right way;let the poor always be treated fairly.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>May the mountains yield prosperity for all,and may the hills be fruitful.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Help him to defend the poor,to rescue the children of the needy,and to crush their oppressors.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>May they fear you as long as the sun shines,as long as the moon remains in the sky.Yes, forever!",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>May the king’s rule be refreshing like spring rain on freshly cut grass,like the showers that water the earth.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>May all the godly flourish during his reign.May there be abundant prosperity until the moon is no more.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>May he reign from sea to sea,and from the Euphrates River to the ends of the earth.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Desert nomads will bow before him;his enemies will fall before him in the dust.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The western kings of Tarshish and other distant landswill bring him tribute.The eastern kings of Sheba and Sebawill bring him gifts.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>All kings will bow before him,and all nations will serve him.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He will rescue the poor when they cry to him;he will help the oppressed, who have no one to defend them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He feels pity for the weak and the needy,and he will rescue them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He will redeem them from oppression and violence,for their lives are precious to him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Long live the king!May the gold of Sheba be given to him.May the people always pray for himand bless him all day long.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>May there be abundant grain throughout the land,flourishing even on the hilltops.May the fruit trees flourish like the trees of Lebanon,and may the people thrive like grass in a field.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>May the king’s name endure forever;may it continue as long as the sun shines.May all nations be blessed through himand bring him praise.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, the God of Israel,who alone does such wonderful things.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Praise his glorious name forever!Let the whole earth be filled with his glory.Amen and amen!",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>(This ends the prayers of David son of Jesse.)"
		},
		"73": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Truly God is good to Israel,to those whose hearts are pure.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But as for me, I almost lost my footing.My feet were slipping, and I was almost gone.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For I envied the proudwhen I saw them prosper despite their wickedness.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They seem to live such painless lives;their bodies are so healthy and strong.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They don’t have troubles like other people;they’re not plagued with problems like everyone else.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They wear pride like a jeweled necklaceand clothe themselves with cruelty.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>These fat cats have everythingtheir hearts could ever wish for!",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They scoff and speak only evil;in their pride they seek to crush others.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They boast against the very heavens,and their words strut throughout the earth.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And so the people are dismayed and confused,drinking in all their words.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“What does God know?” they ask.“Does the Most High even know what’s happening?”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Look at these wicked people—enjoying a life of ease while their riches multiply.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Did I keep my heart pure for nothing?Did I keep myself innocent for no reason?",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>I get nothing but trouble all day long;every morning brings me pain.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>If I had really spoken this way to others,I would have been a traitor to your people.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So I tried to understand why the wicked prosper.But what a difficult task it is!",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then I went into your sanctuary, O God,and I finally understood the destiny of the wicked.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Truly, you put them on a slippery pathand send them sliding over the cliff to destruction.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>In an instant they are destroyed,completely swept away by terrors.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When you arise, O Lord,you will laugh at their silly ideasas a person laughs at dreams in the morning.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then I realized that my heart was bitter,and I was all torn up inside.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>I was so foolish and ignorant—I must have seemed like a senseless animal to you.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Yet I still belong to you;you hold my right hand.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>You guide me with your counsel,leading me to a glorious destiny.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Whom have I in heaven but you?I desire you more than anything on earth.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>My health may fail, and my spirit may grow weak,but God remains the strength of my heart;he is mine forever.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Those who desert him will perish,for you destroy those who abandon you.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>But as for me, how good it is to be near God!I have made the Sovereign <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my shelter,and I will tell everyone about the wonderful things you do."
		},
		"74": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O God, why have you rejected us so long?Why is your anger so intense against the sheep of your own pasture?",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Remember that we are the people you chose long ago,the tribe you redeemed as your own special possession!And remember Jerusalem, your home here on earth.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Walk through the awful ruins of the city;see how the enemy has destroyed your sanctuary.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>There your enemies shouted their victorious battle cries;there they set up their battle standards.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They swung their axeslike woodcutters in a forest.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>With axes and picks,they smashed the carved paneling.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They burned your sanctuary to the ground.They defiled the place that bears your name.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then they thought, “Let’s destroy everything!”So they burned down all the places where God was worshiped.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>We no longer see your miraculous signs.All the prophets are gone,and no one can tell us when it will end.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>How long, O God, will you allow our enemies to insult you?Will you let them dishonor your name forever?",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Why do you hold back your strong right hand?Unleash your powerful fist and destroy them.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>You, O God, are my king from ages past,bringing salvation to the earth.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>You split the sea by your strengthand smashed the heads of the sea monsters.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You crushed the heads of Leviathanand let the desert animals eat him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>You caused the springs and streams to gush forth,and you dried up rivers that never run dry.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Both day and night belong to you;you made the starlight and the sun.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>You set the boundaries of the earth,and you made both summer and winter.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>See how these enemies insult you, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.A foolish nation has dishonored your name.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Don’t let these wild beasts destroy your turtledoves.Don’t forget your suffering people forever.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Remember your covenant promises,for the land is full of darkness and violence!",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Don’t let the downtrodden be humiliated again.Instead, let the poor and needy praise your name.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Arise, O God, and defend your cause.Remember how these fools insult you all day long.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Don’t overlook what your enemies have saidor their growing uproar."
		},
		"75": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>We thank you, O God!We give thanks because you are near.People everywhere tell of your wonderful deeds.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>God says, “At the time I have planned,I will bring justice against the wicked.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When the earth quakes and its people live in turmoil,I am the one who keeps its foundations firm. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“I warned the proud, ‘Stop your boasting!’I told the wicked, ‘Don’t raise your fists!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Don’t raise your fists in defiance at the heavensor speak with such arrogance.’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For no one on earth—from east or west,or even from the wilderness—should raise a defiant fist.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>It is God alone who judges;he decides who will rise and who will fall.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> holds a cup in his handthat is full of foaming wine mixed with spices.He pours out the wine in judgment,and all the wicked must drink it,draining it to the dregs.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But as for me, I will always proclaim what God has done;I will sing praises to the God of Jacob.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For God says, “I will break the strength of the wicked,but I will increase the power of the godly.”"
		},
		"76": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>God is honored in Judah;his name is great in Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Jerusalem is where he lives;Mount Zion is his home.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>There he has broken the fiery arrows of the enemy,the shields and swords and weapons of war. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You are glorious and more majesticthan the everlasting mountains.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Our boldest enemies have been plundered.They lie before us in the sleep of death.No warrior could lift a hand against us.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>At the blast of your breath, O God of Jacob,their horses and chariots lay still.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>No wonder you are greatly feared!Who can stand before you when your anger explodes?",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>From heaven you sentenced your enemies;the earth trembled and stood silent before you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You stand up to judge those who do evil, O God,and to rescue the oppressed of the earth. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Human defiance only enhances your glory,for you use it as a weapon.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Make vows to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and keep them.Let everyone bring tribute to the Awesome One.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For he breaks the pride of princes,and the kings of the earth fear him."
		},
		"77": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>I cry out to God; yes, I shout.Oh, that God would listen to me!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When I was in deep trouble,I searched for the Lord.All night long I prayed, with hands lifted toward heaven,but my soul was not comforted.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I think of God, and I moan,overwhelmed with longing for his help. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You don’t let me sleep.I am too distressed even to pray!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I think of the good old days,long since ended,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>when my nights were filled with joyful songs.I search my soul and ponder the difference now.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Has the Lord rejected me forever?Will he never again be kind to me?",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Is his unfailing love gone forever?Have his promises permanently failed?",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Has God forgotten to be gracious?Has he slammed the door on his compassion? <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And I said, “This is my fate;the Most High has turned his hand against me.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But then I recall all you have done, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;I remember your wonderful deeds of long ago.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They are constantly in my thoughts.I cannot stop thinking about your mighty works.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>O God, your ways are holy.Is there any god as mighty as you?",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You are the God of great wonders!You demonstrate your awesome power among the nations.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>By your strong arm, you redeemed your people,the descendants of Jacob and Joseph. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When the Red Sea saw you, O God,its waters looked and trembled!The sea quaked to its very depths.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The clouds poured down rain;the thunder rumbled in the sky.Your arrows of lightning flashed.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Your thunder roared from the whirlwind;the lightning lit up the world!The earth trembled and shook.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Your road led through the sea,your pathway through the mighty waters—a pathway no one knew was there!",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You led your people along that road like a flock of sheep,with Moses and Aaron as their shepherds."
		},
		"78": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O my people, listen to my instructions.Open your ears to what I am saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>for I will speak to you in a parable.I will teach you hidden lessons from our past—",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>stories we have heard and known,stories our ancestors handed down to us.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>We will not hide these truths from our children;we will tell the next generationabout the glorious deeds of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,about his power and his mighty wonders.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For he issued his laws to Jacob;he gave his instructions to Israel.He commanded our ancestorsto teach them to their children,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>so the next generation might know them—even the children not yet born—and they in turn will teach their own children.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So each generation should set its hope anew on God,not forgetting his glorious miraclesand obeying his commands.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then they will not be like their ancestors—stubborn, rebellious, and unfaithful,refusing to give their hearts to God.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The warriors of Ephraim, though armed with bows,turned their backs and fled on the day of battle.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They did not keep God’s covenantand refused to live by his instructions.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They forgot what he had done—the great wonders he had shown them,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>the miracles he did for their ancestorson the plain of Zoan in the land of Egypt.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>For he divided the sea and led them through,making the water stand up like walls!",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>In the daytime he led them by a cloud,and all night by a pillar of fire.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He split open the rocks in the wildernessto give them water, as from a gushing spring.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He made streams pour from the rock,making the waters flow down like a river!",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Yet they kept on sinning against him,rebelling against the Most High in the desert.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They stubbornly tested God in their hearts,demanding the foods they craved.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They even spoke against God himself, saying,“God can’t give us food in the wilderness.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Yes, he can strike a rock so water gushes out,but he can’t give his people bread and meat.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> heard them, he was furious.The fire of his wrath burned against Jacob.Yes, his anger rose against Israel,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>for they did not believe Godor trust him to care for them.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But he commanded the skies to open;he opened the doors of heaven.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He rained down manna for them to eat;he gave them bread from heaven.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>They ate the food of angels!God gave them all they could hold.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He released the east wind in the heavensand guided the south wind by his mighty power.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>He rained down meat as thick as dust—birds as plentiful as the sand on the seashore!",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He caused the birds to fall within their campand all around their tents.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The people ate their fill.He gave them what they craved.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But before they satisfied their craving,while the meat was yet in their mouths,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>the anger of God rose against them,and he killed their strongest men.He struck down the finest of Israel’s young men.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>But in spite of this, the people kept sinning.Despite his wonders, they refused to trust him.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So he ended their lives in failure,their years in terror.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>When God began killing them,they finally sought him.They repented and took God seriously.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then they remembered that God was their rock,that God Most High was their redeemer.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>But all they gave him was lip service;they lied to him with their tongues.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Their hearts were not loyal to him.They did not keep his covenant.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Yet he was merciful and forgave their sinsand did not destroy them all.Many times he held back his angerand did not unleash his fury!",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>For he remembered that they were merely mortal,gone like a breath of wind that never returns.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Oh, how often they rebelled against him in the wildernessand grieved his heart in that dry wasteland.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Again and again they tested God’s patienceand provoked the Holy One of Israel.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>They did not remember his powerand how he rescued them from their enemies.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>They did not remember his miraculous signs in Egypt,his wonders on the plain of Zoan.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>For he turned their rivers into blood,so no one could drink from the streams.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>He sent vast swarms of flies to consume themand hordes of frogs to ruin them.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>He gave their crops to caterpillars;their harvest was consumed by locusts.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>He destroyed their grapevines with hailand shattered their sycamore-figs with sleet.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>He abandoned their cattle to the hail,their livestock to bolts of lightning.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>He loosed on them his fierce anger—all his fury, rage, and hostility.He dispatched against thema band of destroying angels.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>He turned his anger against them;he did not spare the Egyptians’ livesbut ravaged them with the plague.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>He killed the oldest son in each Egyptian family,the flower of youth throughout the land of Egypt.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>But he led his own people like a flock of sheep,guiding them safely through the wilderness.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>He kept them safe so they were not afraid;but the sea covered their enemies.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>He brought them to the border of his holy land,to this land of hills he had won for them.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>He drove out the nations before them;he gave them their inheritance by lot.He settled the tribes of Israel into their homes.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>But they kept testing and rebelling against God Most High.They did not obey his laws.",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>They turned back and were as faithless as their parents.They were as undependable as a crooked bow.",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>They angered God by building shrines to other gods;they made him jealous with their idols.",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>When God heard them, he was very angry,and he completely rejected Israel.",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>Then he abandoned his dwelling at Shiloh,the Tabernacle where he had lived among the people.",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>He allowed the Ark of his might to be captured;he surrendered his glory into enemy hands.",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>He gave his people over to be butchered by the sword,because he was so angry with his own people—his special possession.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>Their young men were killed by fire;their young women died before singing their wedding songs.",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>Their priests were slaughtered,and their widows could not mourn their deaths.",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>Then the Lord rose up as though waking from sleep,like a warrior aroused from a drunken stupor.",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup>He routed his enemiesand sent them to eternal shame.",
			"67": "<sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup>But he rejected Joseph’s descendants;he did not choose the tribe of Ephraim.",
			"68": "<sup class=\"versenum\">68 </sup>He chose instead the tribe of Judah,and Mount Zion, which he loved.",
			"69": "<sup class=\"versenum\">69 </sup>There he built his sanctuary as high as the heavens,as solid and enduring as the earth.",
			"70": "<sup class=\"versenum\">70 </sup>He chose his servant David,calling him from the sheep pens.",
			"71": "<sup class=\"versenum\">71 </sup>He took David from tending the ewes and lambsand made him the shepherd of Jacob’s descendants—God’s own people, Israel.",
			"72": "<sup class=\"versenum\">72 </sup>He cared for them with a true heartand led them with skillful hands."
		},
		"79": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O God, pagan nations have conquered your land,your special possession.They have defiled your holy Templeand made Jerusalem a heap of ruins.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>They have left the bodies of your servantsas food for the birds of heaven.The flesh of your godly oneshas become food for the wild animals.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Blood has flowed like water all around Jerusalem;no one is left to bury the dead.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>We are mocked by our neighbors,an object of scorn and derision to those around us.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, how long will you be angry with us? Forever?How long will your jealousy burn like fire?",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Pour out your wrath on the nations that refuse to acknowledge you—on kingdoms that do not call upon your name.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For they have devoured your people Israel,making the land a desolate wilderness.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Do not hold us guilty for the sins of our ancestors!Let your compassion quickly meet our needs,for we are on the brink of despair.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Help us, O God of our salvation!Help us for the glory of your name.Save us and forgive our sinsfor the honor of your name.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Why should pagan nations be allowed to scoff,asking, “Where is their God?”Show us your vengeance against the nations,for they have spilled the blood of your servants.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Listen to the moaning of the prisoners.Demonstrate your great power by saving those condemned to die.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>O Lord, pay back our neighbors seven timesfor the scorn they have hurled at you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then we your people, the sheep of your pasture,will thank you forever and ever,praising your greatness from generation to generation."
		},
		"80": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Please listen, O Shepherd of Israel,you who lead Joseph’s descendants like a flock.O God, enthroned above the cherubim,display your radiant glory",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>to Ephraim, Benjamin, and Manasseh.Show us your mighty power.Come to rescue us!",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Turn us again to yourself, O God.Make your face shine down upon us.Only then will we be saved.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Heaven’s Armies,how long will you be angry with our prayers?",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You have fed us with sorrowand made us drink tears by the bucketful.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You have made us the scorn of neighboring nations.Our enemies treat us as a joke.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Turn us again to yourself, O God of Heaven’s Armies.Make your face shine down upon us.Only then will we be saved.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You brought us from Egypt like a grapevine;you drove away the pagan nations and transplanted us into your land.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You cleared the ground for us,and we took root and filled the land.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Our shade covered the mountains;our branches covered the mighty cedars.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>We spread our branches west to the Mediterranean Sea;our shoots spread east to the Euphrates River.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But now, why have you broken down our wallsso that all who pass by may steal our fruit?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The wild boar from the forest devours it,and the wild animals feed on it.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Come back, we beg you, O God of Heaven’s Armies.Look down from heaven and see our plight.Take care of this grapevine",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>that you yourself have planted,this son you have raised for yourself.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For we are chopped up and burned by our enemies.May they perish at the sight of your frown.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Strengthen the man you love,the son of your choice.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then we will never abandon you again.Revive us so we can call on your name once more.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Turn us again to yourself, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Heaven’s Armies.Make your face shine down upon us.Only then will we be saved."
		},
		"81": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Sing praises to God, our strength.Sing to the God of Jacob.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Sing! Beat the tambourine.Play the sweet lyre and the harp.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Blow the ram’s horn at new moon,and again at full moon to call a festival!",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For this is required by the decrees of Israel;it is a regulation of the God of Jacob.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He made it a law for Israelwhen he attacked Egypt to set us free.I heard an unknown voice say,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“Now I will take the load from your shoulders;I will free your hands from their heavy tasks.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>You cried to me in trouble, and I saved you;I answered out of the thundercloudand tested your faith when there was no water at Meribah. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“Listen to me, O my people, while I give you stern warnings.O Israel, if you would only listen to me!",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You must never have a foreign god;you must not bow down before a false god.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For it was I, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God,who rescued you from the land of Egypt.Open your mouth wide, and I will fill it with good things.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“But no, my people wouldn’t listen.Israel did not want me around.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So I let them follow their own stubborn desires,living according to their own ideas.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Oh, that my people would listen to me!Oh, that Israel would follow me, walking in my paths!",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>How quickly I would then subdue their enemies!How soon my hands would be upon their foes!",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Those who hate the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> would cringe before him;they would be doomed forever.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But I would feed you with the finest wheat.I would satisfy you with wild honey from the rock.”"
		},
		"82": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>God presides over heaven’s court;he pronounces judgment on the heavenly beings:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“How long will you hand down unjust decisionsby favoring the wicked? <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Give justice to the poor and the orphan;uphold the rights of the oppressed and the destitute.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Rescue the poor and helpless;deliver them from the grasp of evil people.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But these oppressors know nothing;they are so ignorant!They wander about in darkness,while the whole world is shaken to the core.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I say, ‘You are gods;you are all children of the Most High.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But you will die like mere mortalsand fall like every other ruler.’”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Rise up, O God, and judge the earth,for all the nations belong to you."
		},
		"83": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O God, do not be silent!Do not be deaf.Do not be quiet, O God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Don’t you hear the uproar of your enemies?Don’t you see that your arrogant enemies are rising up?",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They devise crafty schemes against your people;they conspire against your precious ones.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Come,” they say, “let us wipe out Israel as a nation.We will destroy the very memory of its existence.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Yes, this was their unanimous decision.They signed a treaty as allies against you—",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>these Edomites and Ishmaelites;Moabites and Hagrites;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Gebalites, Ammonites, and Amalekites;and people from Philistia and Tyre.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Assyria has joined them, too,and is allied with the descendants of Lot. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Do to them as you did to the Midianitesand as you did to Sisera and Jabin at the Kishon River.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They were destroyed at Endor,and their decaying corpses fertilized the soil.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Let their mighty nobles die as Oreb and Zeeb did.Let all their princes die like Zebah and Zalmunna,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>for they said, “Let us seize for our own usethese pasturelands of God!”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>O my God, scatter them like tumbleweed,like chaff before the wind!",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>As a fire burns a forestand as a flame sets mountains ablaze,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>chase them with your fierce storm;terrify them with your tempest.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Utterly disgrace themuntil they submit to your name, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Let them be ashamed and terrified forever.Let them die in disgrace.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then they will learn that you alone are called the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,that you alone are the Most High,supreme over all the earth."
		},
		"84": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>How lovely is your dwelling place,O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of Heaven’s Armies.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I long, yes, I faint with longingto enter the courts of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.With my whole being, body and soul,I will shout joyfully to the living God.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Even the sparrow finds a home,and the swallow builds her nest and raises her youngat a place near your altar,O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of Heaven’s Armies, my King and my God!",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>What joy for those who can live in your house,always singing your praises. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>What joy for those whose strength comes from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,who have set their minds on a pilgrimage to Jerusalem.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When they walk through the Valley of Weeping,it will become a place of refreshing springs.The autumn rains will clothe it with blessings.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They will continue to grow stronger,and each of them will appear before God in Jerusalem.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Heaven’s Armies, hear my prayer.Listen, O God of Jacob. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>O God, look with favor upon the king, our shield!Show favor to the one you have anointed.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>A single day in your courtsis better than a thousand anywhere else!I would rather be a gatekeeper in the house of my Godthan live the good life in the homes of the wicked.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God is our sun and our shield.He gives us grace and glory.The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will withhold no good thingfrom those who do what is right.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of Heaven’s Armies,what joy for those who trust in you."
		},
		"85": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you poured out blessings on your land!You restored the fortunes of Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>You forgave the guilt of your people—yes, you covered all their sins. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You held back your fury.You kept back your blazing anger.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now restore us again, O God of our salvation.Put aside your anger against us once more.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Will you be angry with us always?Will you prolong your wrath to all generations?",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Won’t you revive us again,so your people can rejoice in you?",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Show us your unfailing love, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,and grant us your salvation.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I listen carefully to what God the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is saying,for he speaks peace to his faithful people.But let them not return to their foolish ways.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Surely his salvation is near to those who fear him,so our land will be filled with his glory.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Unfailing love and truth have met together.Righteousness and peace have kissed!",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Truth springs up from the earth,and righteousness smiles down from heaven.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Yes, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> pours down his blessings.Our land will yield its bountiful harvest.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Righteousness goes as a herald before him,preparing the way for his steps."
		},
		"86": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Bend down, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and hear my prayer;answer me, for I need your help.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Protect me, for I am devoted to you.Save me, for I serve you and trust you.You are my God.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Be merciful to me, O Lord,for I am calling on you constantly.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Give me happiness, O Lord,for I give myself to you.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>O Lord, you are so good, so ready to forgive,so full of unfailing love for all who ask for your help.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Listen closely to my prayer, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;hear my urgent cry.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I will call to you whenever I’m in trouble,and you will answer me.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>No pagan god is like you, O Lord.None can do what you do!",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>All the nations you madewill come and bow before you, Lord;they will praise your holy name.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For you are great and perform wonderful deeds.You alone are God.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Teach me your ways, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,that I may live according to your truth!Grant me purity of heart,so that I may honor you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>With all my heart I will praise you, O Lord my God.I will give glory to your name forever,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>for your love for me is very great.You have rescued me from the depths of death.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>O God, insolent people rise up against me;a violent gang is trying to kill me.You mean nothing to them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But you, O Lord,are a God of compassion and mercy,slow to get angryand filled with unfailing love and faithfulness.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Look down and have mercy on me.Give your strength to your servant;save me, the son of your servant.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Send me a sign of your favor.Then those who hate me will be put to shame,for you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, help and comfort me."
		},
		"87": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>On the holy mountainstands the city founded by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He loves the city of Jerusalemmore than any other city in Israel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>O city of God,what glorious things are said of you! <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I will count Egypt and Babylon among those who know me—also Philistia and Tyre, and even distant Ethiopia.They have all become citizens of Jerusalem!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Regarding Jerusalem it will be said,“Everyone enjoys the rights of citizenship there.”And the Most High will personally bless this city.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> registers the nations, he will say,“They have all become citizens of Jerusalem.” <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The people will play flutes and sing,“The source of my life springs from Jerusalem!”"
		},
		"88": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, God of my salvation,I cry out to you by day.I come to you at night.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now hear my prayer;listen to my cry.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For my life is full of troubles,and death draws near.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I am as good as dead,like a strong man with no strength left.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They have left me among the dead,and I lie like a corpse in a grave.I am forgotten,cut off from your care.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You have thrown me into the lowest pit,into the darkest depths.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Your anger weighs me down;with wave after wave you have engulfed me. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You have driven my friends awayby making me repulsive to them.I am in a trap with no way of escape.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>My eyes are blinded by my tears.Each day I beg for your help, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;I lift my hands to you for mercy.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Are your wonderful deeds of any use to the dead?Do the dead rise up and praise you? <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Can those in the grave declare your unfailing love?Can they proclaim your faithfulness in the place of destruction?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Can the darkness speak of your wonderful deeds?Can anyone in the land of forgetfulness talk about your righteousness?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, I cry out to you.I will keep on pleading day by day.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, why do you reject me?Why do you turn your face from me?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>I have been sick and close to death since my youth.I stand helpless and desperate before your terrors.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Your fierce anger has overwhelmed me.Your terrors have paralyzed me.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They swirl around me like floodwaters all day long.They have engulfed me completely.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>You have taken away my companions and loved ones.Darkness is my closest friend."
		},
		"89": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>I will sing of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s unfailing love forever!Young and old will hear of your faithfulness.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Your unfailing love will last forever.Your faithfulness is as enduring as the heavens.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “I have made a covenant with David, my chosen servant.I have sworn this oath to him:",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>‘I will establish your descendants as kings forever;they will sit on your throne from now until eternity.’” <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>All heaven will praise your great wonders, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;myriads of angels will praise you for your faithfulness.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For who in all of heaven can compare with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?What mightiest angel is anything like the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The highest angelic powers stand in awe of God.He is far more awesome than all who surround his throne.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Heaven’s Armies!Where is there anyone as mighty as you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?You are entirely faithful.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You rule the oceans.You subdue their storm-tossed waves.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You crushed the great sea monster.You scattered your enemies with your mighty arm.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The heavens are yours, and the earth is yours;everything in the world is yours—you created it all.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>You created north and south.Mount Tabor and Mount Hermon praise your name.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Powerful is your arm!Strong is your hand!Your right hand is lifted high in glorious strength.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Righteousness and justice are the foundation of your throne.Unfailing love and truth walk before you as attendants.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Happy are those who hear the joyful call to worship,for they will walk in the light of your presence, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>They rejoice all day long in your wonderful reputation.They exult in your righteousness.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>You are their glorious strength.It pleases you to make us strong.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Yes, our protection comes from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,and he, the Holy One of Israel, has given us our king.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Long ago you spoke in a vision to your faithful people.You said, “I have raised up a warrior.I have selected him from the common people to be king.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>I have found my servant David.I have anointed him with my holy oil.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>I will steady him with my hand;with my powerful arm I will make him strong.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>His enemies will not defeat him,nor will the wicked overpower him.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>I will beat down his adversaries before himand destroy those who hate him.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>My faithfulness and unfailing love will be with him,and by my authority he will grow in power.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>I will extend his rule over the sea,his dominion over the rivers.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And he will call out to me, ‘You are my Father,my God, and the Rock of my salvation.’",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>I will make him my firstborn son,the mightiest king on earth.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>I will love him and be kind to him forever;my covenant with him will never end.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>I will preserve an heir for him;his throne will be as endless as the days of heaven.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But if his descendants forsake my instructionsand fail to obey my regulations,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>if they do not obey my decreesand fail to keep my commands,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>then I will punish their sin with the rod,and their disobedience with beating.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>But I will never stop loving himnor fail to keep my promise to him.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>No, I will not break my covenant;I will not take back a single word I said.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>I have sworn an oath to David,and in my holiness I cannot lie:",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>His dynasty will go on forever;his kingdom will endure as the sun.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>It will be as eternal as the moon,my faithful witness in the sky!” <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>But now you have rejected him and cast him off.You are angry with your anointed king.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>You have renounced your covenant with him;you have thrown his crown in the dust.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>You have broken down the walls protecting himand ruined every fort defending him.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Everyone who comes along has robbed him,and he has become a joke to his neighbors.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>You have strengthened his enemiesand made them all rejoice.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>You have made his sword uselessand refused to help him in battle.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>You have ended his splendorand overturned his throne.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>You have made him old before his timeand publicly disgraced him. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, how long will this go on?Will you hide yourself forever?How long will your anger burn like fire?",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Remember how short my life is,how empty and futile this human existence!",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>No one can live forever; all will die.No one can escape the power of the grave. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Lord, where is your unfailing love?You promised it to David with a faithful pledge.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Consider, Lord, how your servants are disgraced!I carry in my heart the insults of so many people.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Your enemies have mocked me, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;they mock your anointed king wherever he goes.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> forever!Amen and amen!"
		},
		"90": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Lord, through all the generationsyou have been our home!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Before the mountains were born,before you gave birth to the earth and the world,from beginning to end, you are God.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You turn people back to dust, saying,“Return to dust, you mortals!”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For you, a thousand years are as a passing day,as brief as a few night hours.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You sweep people away like dreams that disappear.They are like grass that springs up in the morning.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>In the morning it blooms and flourishes,but by evening it is dry and withered.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>We wither beneath your anger;we are overwhelmed by your fury.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You spread out our sins before you—our secret sins—and you see them all.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>We live our lives beneath your wrath,ending our years with a groan.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Seventy years are given to us!Some even live to eighty.But even the best years are filled with pain and trouble;soon they disappear, and we fly away.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Who can comprehend the power of your anger?Your wrath is as awesome as the fear you deserve.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Teach us to realize the brevity of life,so that we may grow in wisdom.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, come back to us!How long will you delay?Take pity on your servants!",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Satisfy us each morning with your unfailing love,so we may sing for joy to the end of our lives.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Give us gladness in proportion to our former misery!Replace the evil years with good.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Let us, your servants, see you work again;let our children see your glory.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And may the Lord our God show us his approvaland make our efforts successful.Yes, make our efforts successful!"
		},
		"91": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Those who live in the shelter of the Most Highwill find rest in the shadow of the Almighty.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>This I declare about the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>:He alone is my refuge, my place of safety;he is my God, and I trust him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For he will rescue you from every trapand protect you from deadly disease.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He will cover you with his feathers.He will shelter you with his wings.His faithful promises are your armor and protection.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Do not be afraid of the terrors of the night,nor the arrow that flies in the day.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Do not dread the disease that stalks in darkness,nor the disaster that strikes at midday.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Though a thousand fall at your side,though ten thousand are dying around you,these evils will not touch you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Just open your eyes,and see how the wicked are punished.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>If you make the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your refuge,if you make the Most High your shelter,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>no evil will conquer you;no plague will come near your home.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>For he will order his angelsto protect you wherever you go.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They will hold you up with their handsso you won’t even hurt your foot on a stone.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>You will trample upon lions and cobras;you will crush fierce lions and serpents under your feet!",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says, “I will rescue those who love me.I will protect those who trust in my name.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When they call on me, I will answer;I will be with them in trouble.I will rescue and honor them.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>I will reward them with a long lifeand give them my salvation.”"
		},
		"92": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>It is good to give thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,to sing praises to the Most High.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>It is good to proclaim your unfailing love in the morning,your faithfulness in the evening,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>accompanied by a ten-stringed instrument, a harp,and the melody of a lyre.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You thrill me, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, with all you have done for me!I sing for joy because of what you have done.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, what great works you do!And how deep are your thoughts.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Only a simpleton would not know,and only a fool would not understand this:",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Though the wicked sprout like weedsand evildoers flourish,they will be destroyed forever.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, will be exalted forever.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Your enemies, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, will surely perish;all evildoers will be scattered.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But you have made me as strong as a wild ox.You have anointed me with the finest oil.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>My eyes have seen the downfall of my enemies;my ears have heard the defeat of my wicked opponents.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But the godly will flourish like palm treesand grow strong like the cedars of Lebanon.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>For they are transplanted to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s own house.They flourish in the courts of our God.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Even in old age they will still produce fruit;they will remain vital and green.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>They will declare, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is just!He is my rock!There is no evil in him!”"
		},
		"93": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is king! He is robed in majesty.Indeed, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is robed in majesty and armed with strength.The world stands firmand cannot be shaken.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Your throne, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, has stood from time immemorial.You yourself are from the everlasting past.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The floods have risen up, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.The floods have roared like thunder;the floods have lifted their pounding waves.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But mightier than the violent raging of the seas,mightier than the breakers on the shore—the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> above is mightier than these!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Your royal laws cannot be changed.Your reign, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, is holy forever and ever."
		},
		"94": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of vengeance,O God of vengeance, let your glorious justice shine forth!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Arise, O Judge of the earth.Give the proud what they deserve.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>How long, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?How long will the wicked be allowed to gloat?",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>How long will they speak with arrogance?How long will these evil people boast?",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They crush your people, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,hurting those you claim as your own.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They kill widows and foreignersand murder orphans.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> isn’t looking,” they say,“and besides, the God of Israel doesn’t care.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Think again, you fools!When will you finally catch on?",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Is he deaf—the one who made your ears?Is he blind—the one who formed your eyes?",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He punishes the nations—won’t he also punish you?He knows everything—doesn’t he also know what you are doing?",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> knows people’s thoughts;he knows they are worthless!",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Joyful are those you discipline, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,those you teach with your instructions.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>You give them relief from troubled timesuntil a pit is dug to capture the wicked.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will not reject his people;he will not abandon his special possession.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Judgment will again be founded on justice,and those with virtuous hearts will pursue it.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Who will protect me from the wicked?Who will stand up for me against evildoers?",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Unless the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had helped me,I would soon have settled in the silence of the grave.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>I cried out, “I am slipping!”but your unfailing love, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, supported me.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When doubts filled my mind,your comfort gave me renewed hope and cheer.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Can unjust leaders claim that God is on their side—leaders whose decrees permit injustice?",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They gang up against the righteousand condemn the innocent to death.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is my fortress;my God is the mighty rock where I hide.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>God will turn the sins of evil people back on them.He will destroy them for their sins.The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God will destroy them."
		},
		"95": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Come, let us sing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!Let us shout joyfully to the Rock of our salvation.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Let us come to him with thanksgiving.Let us sing psalms of praise to him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is a great God,a great King above all gods.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He holds in his hands the depths of the earthand the mightiest mountains.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The sea belongs to him, for he made it.His hands formed the dry land, too.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Come, let us worship and bow down.Let us kneel before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our maker,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>for he is our God.We are the people he watches over,the flock under his care.If only you would listen to his voice today!",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says, “Don’t harden your hearts as Israel did at Meribah,as they did at Massah in the wilderness.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For there your ancestors tested and tried my patience,even though they saw everything I did.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For forty years I was angry with them, and I said,‘They are a people whose hearts turn away from me.They refuse to do what I tell them.’",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So in my anger I took an oath:‘They will never enter my place of rest.’”"
		},
		"96": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Sing a new song to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!Let the whole earth sing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Sing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; praise his name.Each day proclaim the good news that he saves.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Publish his glorious deeds among the nations.Tell everyone about the amazing things he does.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Great is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>! He is most worthy of praise!He is to be feared above all gods.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The gods of other nations are mere idols,but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made the heavens!",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Honor and majesty surround him;strength and beauty fill his sanctuary.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>O nations of the world, recognize the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;recognize that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is glorious and strong.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Give to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the glory he deserves!Bring your offering and come into his courts.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in all his holy splendor.Let all the earth tremble before him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Tell all the nations, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> reigns!”The world stands firm and cannot be shaken.He will judge all peoples fairly.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Let the heavens be glad, and the earth rejoice!Let the sea and everything in it shout his praise!",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Let the fields and their crops burst out with joy!Let the trees of the forest sing for joy",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for he is coming!He is coming to judge the earth.He will judge the world with justice,and the nations with his truth."
		},
		"97": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is king!Let the earth rejoice!Let the farthest coastlands be glad.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Dark clouds surround him.Righteousness and justice are the foundation of his throne.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Fire spreads ahead of himand burns up all his foes.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>His lightning flashes out across the world.The earth sees and trembles.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The mountains melt like wax before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,before the Lord of all the earth.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The heavens proclaim his righteousness;every nation sees his glory.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Those who worship idols are disgraced—all who brag about their worthless gods—for every god must bow to him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Jerusalem has heard and rejoiced,and all the towns of Judah are gladbecause of your justice, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, are supreme over all the earth;you are exalted far above all gods.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You who love the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, hate evil!He protects the lives of his godly peopleand rescues them from the power of the wicked.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Light shines on the godly,and joy on those whose hearts are right.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>May all who are godly rejoice in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>and praise his holy name!"
		},
		"98": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Sing a new song to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,for he has done wonderful deeds.His right hand has won a mighty victory;his holy arm has shown his saving power!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has announced his victoryand has revealed his righteousness to every nation!",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He has remembered his promise to love and be faithful to Israel.The ends of the earth have seen the victory of our God.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Shout to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, all the earth;break out in praise and sing for joy!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Sing your praise to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with the harp,with the harp and melodious song,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>with trumpets and the sound of the ram’s horn.Make a joyful symphony before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the King!",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Let the sea and everything in it shout his praise!Let the earth and all living things join in.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Let the rivers clap their hands in glee!Let the hills sing out their songs of joy",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,for he is coming to judge the earth.He will judge the world with justice,and the nations with fairness."
		},
		"99": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is king!Let the nations tremble!He sits on his throne between the cherubim.Let the whole earth quake!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sits in majesty in Jerusalem,exalted above all the nations.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Let them praise your great and awesome name.Your name is holy!",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Mighty King, lover of justice,you have established fairness.You have acted with justiceand righteousness throughout Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Exalt the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God!Bow low before his feet, for he is holy!",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Moses and Aaron were among his priests;Samuel also called on his name.They cried to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for help,and he answered them.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He spoke to Israel from the pillar of cloud,and they followed the laws and decrees he gave them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, you answered them.You were a forgiving God to them,but you punished them when they went wrong.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Exalt the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God,and worship at his holy mountain in Jerusalem,for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God is holy!"
		},
		"100": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Shout with joy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, all the earth!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with gladness.Come before him, singing with joy.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Acknowledge that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is God!He made us, and we are his.We are his people, the sheep of his pasture.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Enter his gates with thanksgiving;go into his courts with praise.Give thanks to him and praise his name.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is good.His unfailing love continues forever,and his faithfulness continues to each generation."
		},
		"101": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>I will sing of your love and justice, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.I will praise you with songs.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I will be careful to live a blameless life—when will you come to help me?I will lead a life of integrityin my own home.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I will refuse to look atanything vile and vulgar.I hate all who deal crookedly;I will have nothing to do with them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I will reject perverse ideasand stay away from every evil.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I will not tolerate people who slander their neighbors.I will not endure conceit and pride.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I will search for faithful peopleto be my companions.Only those who are above reproachwill be allowed to serve me.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I will not allow deceivers to serve in my house,and liars will not stay in my presence.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>My daily task will be to ferret out the wickedand free the city of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> from their grip."
		},
		"102": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, hear my prayer!Listen to my plea!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Don’t turn away from mein my time of distress.Bend down to listen,and answer me quickly when I call to you.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For my days disappear like smoke,and my bones burn like red-hot coals.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>My heart is sick, withered like grass,and I have lost my appetite.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Because of my groaning,I am reduced to skin and bones.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I am like an owl in the desert,like a little owl in a far-off wilderness.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I lie awake,lonely as a solitary bird on the roof.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>My enemies taunt me day after day.They mock and curse me.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>I eat ashes for food.My tears run down into my drink",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>because of your anger and wrath.For you have picked me up and thrown me out.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>My life passes as swiftly as the evening shadows.I am withering away like grass.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, will sit on your throne forever.Your fame will endure to every generation.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>You will arise and have mercy on Jerusalem—and now is the time to pity her,now is the time you promised to help.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>For your people love every stone in her wallsand cherish even the dust in her streets.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the nations will tremble before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.The kings of the earth will tremble before his glory.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will rebuild Jerusalem.He will appear in his glory.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He will listen to the prayers of the destitute.He will not reject their pleas.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Let this be recorded for future generations,so that a people not yet born will praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Tell them the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> looked downfrom his heavenly sanctuary.He looked down to earth from heaven",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>to hear the groans of the prisoners,to release those condemned to die.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And so the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s fame will be celebrated in Zion,his praises in Jerusalem,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>when multitudes gather togetherand kingdoms come to worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He broke my strength in midlife,cutting short my days.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But I cried to him, “O my God, who lives forever,don’t take my life while I am so young!",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Long ago you laid the foundation of the earthand made the heavens with your hands.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>They will perish, but you remain forever;they will wear out like old clothing.You will change them like a garmentand discard them.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But you are always the same;you will live forever.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The children of your peoplewill live in security.Their children’s childrenwill thrive in your presence.”"
		},
		"103": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Let all that I am praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;with my whole heart, I will praise his holy name.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Let all that I am praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;may I never forget the good things he does for me.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He forgives all my sinsand heals all my diseases.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He redeems me from deathand crowns me with love and tender mercies.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He fills my life with good things.My youth is renewed like the eagle’s!",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gives righteousnessand justice to all who are treated unfairly.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He revealed his character to Mosesand his deeds to the people of Israel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is compassionate and merciful,slow to get angry and filled with unfailing love.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He will not constantly accuse us,nor remain angry forever.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He does not punish us for all our sins;he does not deal harshly with us, as we deserve.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>For his unfailing love toward those who fear himis as great as the height of the heavens above the earth.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He has removed our sins as far from usas the east is from the west.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is like a father to his children,tender and compassionate to those who fear him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>For he knows how weak we are;he remembers we are only dust.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Our days on earth are like grass;like wildflowers, we bloom and die.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The wind blows, and we are gone—as though we had never been here.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But the love of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> remains foreverwith those who fear him.His salvation extends to the children’s children",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>of those who are faithful to his covenant,of those who obey his commandments!",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has made the heavens his throne;from there he rules over everything.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you angels,you mighty ones who carry out his plans,listening for each of his commands.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Yes, praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you armies of angelswho serve him and do his will!",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, everything he has created,everything in all his kingdom.Let all that I am praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"104": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Let all that I am praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, how great you are!You are robed with honor and majesty.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>You are dressed in a robe of light.You stretch out the starry curtain of the heavens;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>you lay out the rafters of your home in the rain clouds.You make the clouds your chariot;you ride upon the wings of the wind.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The winds are your messengers;flames of fire are your servants.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You placed the world on its foundationso it would never be moved.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You clothed the earth with floods of water,water that covered even the mountains.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>At your command, the water fled;at the sound of your thunder, it hurried away.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Mountains rose and valleys sankto the levels you decreed.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then you set a firm boundary for the seas,so they would never again cover the earth.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You make springs pour water into the ravines,so streams gush down from the mountains.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They provide water for all the animals,and the wild donkeys quench their thirst.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The birds nest beside the streamsand sing among the branches of the trees.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>You send rain on the mountains from your heavenly home,and you fill the earth with the fruit of your labor.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You cause grass to grow for the livestockand plants for people to use.You allow them to produce food from the earth—",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>wine to make them glad,olive oil to soothe their skin,and bread to give them strength.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The trees of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> are well cared for—the cedars of Lebanon that he planted.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>There the birds make their nests,and the storks make their homes in the cypresses.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>High in the mountains live the wild goats,and the rocks form a refuge for the hyraxes.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>You made the moon to mark the seasons,and the sun knows when to set.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You send the darkness, and it becomes night,when all the forest animals prowl about.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the young lions roar for their prey,stalking the food provided by God.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>At dawn they slink backinto their dens to rest.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then people go off to their work,where they labor until evening.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, what a variety of things you have made!In wisdom you have made them all.The earth is full of your creatures.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Here is the ocean, vast and wide,teeming with life of every kind,both large and small.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>See the ships sailing along,and Leviathan, which you made to play in the sea.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>They all depend on youto give them food as they need it.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>When you supply it, they gather it.You open your hand to feed them,and they are richly satisfied.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But if you turn away from them, they panic.When you take away their breath,they die and turn again to dust.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>When you give them your breath, life is created,and you renew the face of the earth.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>May the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> continue forever!The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> takes pleasure in all he has made!",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The earth trembles at his glance;the mountains smoke at his touch.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>I will sing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as long as I live.I will praise my God to my last breath!",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>May all my thoughts be pleasing to him,for I rejoice in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Let all sinners vanish from the face of the earth;let the wicked disappear forever.Let all that I am praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!"
		},
		"105": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Give thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and proclaim his greatness.Let the whole world know what he has done.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Sing to him; yes, sing his praises.Tell everyone about his wonderful deeds.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Exult in his holy name;rejoice, you who worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Search for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and for his strength;continually seek him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Remember the wonders he has performed,his miracles, and the rulings he has given,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>you children of his servant Abraham,you descendants of Jacob, his chosen ones.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God.His justice is seen throughout the land.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He always stands by his covenant—the commitment he made to a thousand generations.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>This is the covenant he made with Abrahamand the oath he swore to Isaac.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He confirmed it to Jacob as a decree,and to the people of Israel as a never-ending covenant:",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“I will give you the land of Canaanas your special possession.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He said this when they were few in number,a tiny group of strangers in Canaan.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>They wandered from nation to nation,from one kingdom to another.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Yet he did not let anyone oppress them.He warned kings on their behalf:",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“Do not touch my chosen people,and do not hurt my prophets.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He called for a famine on the land of Canaan,cutting off its food supply.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then he sent someone to Egypt ahead of them—Joseph, who was sold as a slave.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They bruised his feet with fettersand placed his neck in an iron collar.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Until the time came to fulfill his dreams,the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> tested Joseph’s character.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Pharaoh sent for him and set him free;the ruler of the nation opened his prison door.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Joseph was put in charge of all the king’s household;he became ruler over all the king’s possessions.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He could instruct the king’s aides as he pleasedand teach the king’s advisers.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Israel arrived in Egypt;Jacob lived as a foreigner in the land of Ham.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> multiplied the people of Israeluntil they became too mighty for their enemies.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then he turned the Egyptians against the Israelites,and they plotted against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s servants.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent his servant Moses,along with Aaron, whom he had chosen.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>They performed miraculous signs among the Egyptians,and wonders in the land of Ham.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> blanketed Egypt in darkness,for they had defied his commands to let his people go.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>He turned their water into blood,poisoning all the fish.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then frogs overran the landand even invaded the king’s bedrooms.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke, flies descended on the Egyptians,and gnats swarmed across Egypt.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>He sent them hail instead of rain,and lightning flashed over the land.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He ruined their grapevines and fig treesand shattered all the trees.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>He spoke, and hordes of locusts came—young locusts beyond number.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>They ate up everything green in the land,destroying all the crops in their fields.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then he killed the oldest son in each Egyptian home,the pride and joy of each family.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought his people out of Egypt, loaded with silver and gold;and not one among the tribes of Israel even stumbled.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Egypt was glad when they were gone,for they feared them greatly.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spread a cloud above them as a coveringand gave them a great fire to light the darkness.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>They asked for meat, and he sent them quail;he satisfied their hunger with manna—bread from heaven.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>He split open a rock, and water gushed outto form a river through the dry wasteland.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>For he remembered his sacred promiseto his servant Abraham.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>So he brought his people out of Egypt with joy,his chosen ones with rejoicing.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>He gave his people the lands of pagan nations,and they harvested crops that others had planted.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>All this happened so they would follow his decreesand obey his instructions.Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!"
		},
		"106": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!Give thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for he is good!His faithful love endures forever.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Who can list the glorious miracles of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?Who can ever praise him enough?",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>There is joy for those who deal justly with othersand always do what is right.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Remember me, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, when you show favor to your people;come near and rescue me.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Let me share in the prosperity of your chosen ones.Let me rejoice in the joy of your people;let me praise you with those who are your heritage.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Like our ancestors, we have sinned.We have done wrong! We have acted wickedly!",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Our ancestors in Egyptwere not impressed by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s miraculous deeds.They soon forgot his many acts of kindness to them.Instead, they rebelled against him at the Red Sea.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Even so, he saved them—to defend the honor of his nameand to demonstrate his mighty power.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He commanded the Red Sea to dry up.He led Israel across the sea as if it were a desert.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So he rescued them from their enemiesand redeemed them from their foes.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then the water returned and covered their enemies;not one of them survived.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then his people believed his promises.Then they sang his praise.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Yet how quickly they forgot what he had done!They wouldn’t wait for his counsel!",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>In the wilderness their desires ran wild,testing God’s patience in that dry wasteland.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So he gave them what they asked for,but he sent a plague along with it.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The people in the camp were jealous of Mosesand envious of Aaron, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s holy priest.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Because of this, the earth opened up;it swallowed Dathanand buried Abiram and the other rebels.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Fire fell upon their followers;a flame consumed the wicked.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The people made a calf at Mount Sinai;they bowed before an image made of gold.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>They traded their glorious Godfor a statue of a grass-eating bull.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They forgot God, their savior,who had done such great things in Egypt—",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>such wonderful things in the land of Ham,such awesome deeds at the Red Sea.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So he declared he would destroy them.But Moses, his chosen one, stepped between the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the people.He begged him to turn from his anger and not destroy them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The people refused to enter the pleasant land,for they wouldn’t believe his promise to care for them.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Instead, they grumbled in their tentsand refused to obey the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Therefore, he solemnly sworethat he would kill them in the wilderness,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>that he would scatter their descendants among the nations,exiling them to distant lands.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then our ancestors joined in the worship of Baal at Peor;they even ate sacrifices offered to the dead!",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>They angered the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with all these things,so a plague broke out among them.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But Phinehas had the courage to intervene,and the plague was stopped.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>So he has been regarded as a righteous manever since that time.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>At Meribah, too, they angered the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,causing Moses serious trouble.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>They made Moses angry,and he spoke foolishly.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Israel failed to destroy the nations in the land,as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded them.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Instead, they mingled among the pagansand adopted their evil customs.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>They worshiped their idols,which led to their downfall.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>They even sacrificed their sonsand their daughters to the demons.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>They shed innocent blood,the blood of their sons and daughters.By sacrificing them to the idols of Canaan,they polluted the land with murder.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>They defiled themselves by their evil deeds,and their love of idols was adultery in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s sight.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>That is why the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anger burned against his people,and he abhorred his own special possession.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>He handed them over to pagan nations,and they were ruled by those who hated them.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Their enemies crushed themand brought them under their cruel power.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Again and again he rescued them,but they chose to rebel against him,and they were finally destroyed by their sin.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Even so, he pitied them in their distressand listened to their cries.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>He remembered his covenant with themand relented because of his unfailing love.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>He even caused their captorsto treat them with kindness.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Save us, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God!Gather us back from among the nations,so we can thank your holy nameand rejoice and praise you.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel,who lives from everlasting to everlasting!Let all the people say, “Amen!”Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!"
		},
		"107": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Give thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for he is good!His faithful love endures forever.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Has the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> redeemed you? Then speak out!Tell others he has redeemed you from your enemies.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For he has gathered the exiles from many lands,from east and west,from north and south.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Some wandered in the wilderness,lost and homeless.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Hungry and thirsty,they nearly died.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, help!” they cried in their trouble,and he rescued them from their distress.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He led them straight to safety,to a city where they could live.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Let them praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for his great loveand for the wonderful things he has done for them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For he satisfies the thirstyand fills the hungry with good things.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Some sat in darkness and deepest gloom,imprisoned in iron chains of misery.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They rebelled against the words of God,scorning the counsel of the Most High.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>That is why he broke them with hard labor;they fell, and no one was there to help them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, help!” they cried in their trouble,and he saved them from their distress.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He led them from the darkness and deepest gloom;he snapped their chains.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Let them praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for his great loveand for the wonderful things he has done for them.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For he broke down their prison gates of bronze;he cut apart their bars of iron.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Some were fools; they rebelledand suffered for their sins.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They couldn’t stand the thought of food,and they were knocking on death’s door.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, help!” they cried in their trouble,and he saved them from their distress.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He sent out his word and healed them,snatching them from the door of death.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Let them praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for his great loveand for the wonderful things he has done for them.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Let them offer sacrifices of thanksgivingand sing joyfully about his glorious acts.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Some went off to sea in ships,plying the trade routes of the world.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>They, too, observed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s power in action,his impressive works on the deepest seas.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He spoke, and the winds rose,stirring up the waves.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Their ships were tossed to the heavensand plunged again to the depths;the sailors cringed in terror.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>They reeled and staggered like drunkardsand were at their wits’ end.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, help!” they cried in their trouble,and he saved them from their distress.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>He calmed the storm to a whisperand stilled the waves.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>What a blessing was that stillnessas he brought them safely into harbor!",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Let them praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for his great loveand for the wonderful things he has done for them.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Let them exalt him publicly before the congregationand before the leaders of the nation.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He changes rivers into deserts,and springs of water into dry, thirsty land.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>He turns the fruitful land into salty wastelands,because of the wickedness of those who live there.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>But he also turns deserts into pools of water,the dry land into springs of water.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>He brings the hungry to settle thereand to build their cities.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>They sow their fields, plant their vineyards,and harvest their bumper crops.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>How he blesses them!They raise large families there,and their herds of livestock increase.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>When they decrease in number and become impoverishedthrough oppression, trouble, and sorrow,",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> pours contempt on their princes,causing them to wander in trackless wastelands.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>But he rescues the poor from troubleand increases their families like flocks of sheep.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>The godly will see these things and be glad,while the wicked are struck silent.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Those who are wise will take all this to heart;they will see in our history the faithful love of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"108": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>My heart is confident in you, O God;no wonder I can sing your praises with all my heart!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Wake up, lyre and harp!I will wake the dawn with my song.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I will thank you, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, among all the people.I will sing your praises among the nations.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For your unfailing love is higher than the heavens.Your faithfulness reaches to the clouds.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Be exalted, O God, above the highest heavens.May your glory shine over all the earth.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now rescue your beloved people.Answer and save us by your power.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>God has promised this by his holiness:“I will divide up Shechem with joy.I will measure out the valley of Succoth.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Gilead is mine,and Manasseh, too.Ephraim, my helmet, will produce my warriors,and Judah, my scepter, will produce my kings.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But Moab, my washbasin, will become my servant,and I will wipe my feet on Edomand shout in triumph over Philistia.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Who will bring me into the fortified city?Who will bring me victory over Edom?",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Have you rejected us, O God?Will you no longer march with our armies?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Oh, please help us against our enemies,for all human help is useless.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>With God’s help we will do mighty things,for he will trample down our foes."
		},
		"109": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O God, whom I praise,don’t stand silent and aloof",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>while the wicked slander meand tell lies about me.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They surround me with hateful wordsand fight against me for no reason.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I love them, but they try to destroy me with accusationseven as I am praying for them!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They repay evil for good,and hatred for my love.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They say, “Get an evil person to turn against him.Send an accuser to bring him to trial.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When his case comes up for judgment,let him be pronounced guilty.Count his prayers as sins.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Let his years be few;let someone else take his position.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>May his children become fatherless,and his wife a widow.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>May his children wander as beggarsand be driven from their ruined homes.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>May creditors seize his entire estate,and strangers take all he has earned.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Let no one be kind to him;let no one pity his fatherless children.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>May all his offspring die.May his family name be blotted out in the next generation.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> never forget the sins of his fathers;may his mother’s sins never be erased from the record.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> always remember these sins,and may his name disappear from human memory.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For he refused all kindness to others;he persecuted the poor and needy,and he hounded the brokenhearted to death.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He loved to curse others;now you curse him.He never blessed others;now don’t you bless him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Cursing is as natural to him as his clothing,or the water he drinks,or the rich food he eats.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now may his curses return and cling to him like clothing;may they be tied around him like a belt.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>May those curses become the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s punishmentfor my accusers who speak evil of me.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But deal well with me, O Sovereign <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,for the sake of your own reputation!Rescue mebecause you are so faithful and good.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For I am poor and needy,and my heart is full of pain.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>I am fading like a shadow at dusk;I am brushed off like a locust.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>My knees are weak from fasting,and I am skin and bones.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>I am a joke to people everywhere;when they see me, they shake their heads in scorn.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Help me, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God!Save me because of your unfailing love.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Let them see that this is your doing,that you yourself have done it, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then let them curse me if they like,but you will bless me!When they attack me, they will be disgraced!But I, your servant, will go right on rejoicing!",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>May my accusers be clothed with disgrace;may their humiliation cover them like a cloak.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But I will give repeated thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,praising him to everyone.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>For he stands beside the needy,ready to save them from those who condemn them."
		},
		"110": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to my Lord,“Sit in the place of honor at my right handuntil I humble your enemies,making them a footstool under your feet.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will extend your powerful kingdom from Jerusalem;you will rule over your enemies.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When you go to war,your people will serve you willingly.You are arrayed in holy garments,and your strength will be renewed each day like the morning dew.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has taken an oath and will not break his vow:“You are a priest forever in the order of Melchizedek.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The Lord stands at your right hand to protect you.He will strike down many kings when his anger erupts.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He will punish the nationsand fill their lands with corpses;he will shatter heads over the whole earth.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But he himself will be refreshed from brooks along the way.He will be victorious."
		},
		"111": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!I will thank the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with all my heartas I meet with his godly people.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>How amazing are the deeds of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!All who delight in him should ponder them.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Everything he does reveals his glory and majesty.His righteousness never fails.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He causes us to remember his wonderful works.How gracious and merciful is our <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He gives food to those who fear him;he always remembers his covenant.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He has shown his great power to his peopleby giving them the lands of other nations.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>All he does is just and good,and all his commandments are trustworthy.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They are forever true,to be obeyed faithfully and with integrity.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He has paid a full ransom for his people.He has guaranteed his covenant with them forever.What a holy, awe-inspiring name he has!",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Fear of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is the foundation of true wisdom.All who obey his commandments will grow in wisdom.Praise him forever!"
		},
		"112": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!How joyful are those who fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>and delight in obeying his commands.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Their children will be successful everywhere;an entire generation of godly people will be blessed.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They themselves will be wealthy,and their good deeds will last forever.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Light shines in the darkness for the godly.They are generous, compassionate, and righteous.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Good comes to those who lend money generouslyand conduct their business fairly.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Such people will not be overcome by evil.Those who are righteous will be long remembered.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They do not fear bad news;they confidently trust the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to care for them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They are confident and fearlessand can face their foes triumphantly.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They share freely and give generously to those in need.Their good deeds will be remembered forever.They will have influence and honor.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The wicked will see this and be infuriated.They will grind their teeth in anger;they will slink away, their hopes thwarted."
		},
		"113": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!Yes, give praise, O servants of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.Praise the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Blessed be the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>now and forever.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Everywhere—from east to west—praise the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is high above the nations;his glory is higher than the heavens.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Who can be compared with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God,who is enthroned on high?",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He stoops to look downon heaven and on earth.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He lifts the poor from the dustand the needy from the garbage dump.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He sets them among princes,even the princes of his own people!",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He gives the childless woman a family,making her a happy mother.Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!"
		},
		"114": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>When the Israelites escaped from Egypt—when the family of Jacob left that foreign land—",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>the land of Judah became God’s sanctuary,and Israel became his kingdom.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The Red Sea saw them coming and hurried out of their way!The water of the Jordan River turned away.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The mountains skipped like rams,the hills like lambs!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>What’s wrong, Red Sea, that made you hurry out of their way?What happened, Jordan River, that you turned away?",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Why, mountains, did you skip like rams?Why, hills, like lambs?",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Tremble, O earth, at the presence of the Lord,at the presence of the God of Jacob.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He turned the rock into a pool of water;yes, a spring of water flowed from solid rock."
		},
		"115": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Not to us, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, not to us,but to your name goes all the gloryfor your unfailing love and faithfulness.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Why let the nations say,“Where is their God?”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Our God is in the heavens,and he does as he wishes.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Their idols are merely things of silver and gold,shaped by human hands.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They have mouths but cannot speak,and eyes but cannot see.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They have ears but cannot hear,and noses but cannot smell.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They have hands but cannot feel,and feet but cannot walk,and throats but cannot make a sound.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And those who make idols are just like them,as are all who trust in them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>O Israel, trust the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!He is your helper and your shield.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>O priests, descendants of Aaron, trust the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!He is your helper and your shield.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>All you who fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, trust the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!He is your helper and your shield.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> remembers us and will bless us.He will bless the people of Israeland bless the priests, the descendants of Aaron.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He will bless those who fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,both great and lowly.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> richly blessboth you and your children.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>May you be blessed by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,who made heaven and earth.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The heavens belong to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,but he has given the earth to all humanity.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The dead cannot sing praises to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,for they have gone into the silence of the grave.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But we can praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>both now and forever!Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!"
		},
		"116": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>I love the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> because he hears my voiceand my prayer for mercy.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Because he bends down to listen,I will pray as long as I have breath!",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Death wrapped its ropes around me;the terrors of the grave overtook me.I saw only trouble and sorrow.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then I called on the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>:“Please, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, save me!”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>How kind the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is! How good he is!So merciful, this God of ours!",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> protects those of childlike faith;I was facing death, and he saved me.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Let my soul be at rest again,for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has been good to me.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He has saved me from death,my eyes from tears,my feet from stumbling.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And so I walk in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s presenceas I live here on earth!",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>I believed in you, so I said,“I am deeply troubled, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>In my anxiety I cried out to you,“These people are all liars!”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>What can I offer the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>for all he has done for me?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I will lift up the cup of salvationand praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s name for saving me.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>I will keep my promises to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>in the presence of all his people.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> cares deeplywhen his loved ones die.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, I am your servant;yes, I am your servant, born into your household;you have freed me from my chains.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I will offer you a sacrifice of thanksgivingand call on the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>I will fulfill my vows to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>in the presence of all his people—",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>in the heart of Jerusalem.Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!"
		},
		"117": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, all you nations.Praise him, all you people of the earth.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>For his unfailing love for us is powerful;the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s faithfulness endures forever.Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!"
		},
		"118": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Give thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for he is good!His faithful love endures forever.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Let all Israel repeat:“His faithful love endures forever.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Let Aaron’s descendants, the priests, repeat:“His faithful love endures forever.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Let all who fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> repeat:“His faithful love endures forever.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>In my distress I prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> answered me and set me free.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is for me, so I will have no fear.What can mere people do to me?",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Yes, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is for me; he will help me.I will look in triumph at those who hate me.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>It is better to take refuge in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>than to trust in people.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>It is better to take refuge in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>than to trust in princes.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Though hostile nations surrounded me,I destroyed them all with the authority of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Yes, they surrounded and attacked me,but I destroyed them all with the authority of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They swarmed around me like bees;they blazed against me like a crackling fire.But I destroyed them all with the authority of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>My enemies did their best to kill me,but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rescued me.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is my strength and my song;he has given me victory.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Songs of joy and victory are sung in the camp of the godly.The strong right arm of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has done glorious things!",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The strong right arm of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is raised in triumph.The strong right arm of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has done glorious things!",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I will not die; instead, I will liveto tell what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has done.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has punished me severely,but he did not let me die.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Open for me the gates where the righteous enter,and I will go in and thank the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>These gates lead to the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,and the godly enter there.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>I thank you for answering my prayerand giving me victory!",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The stone that the builders rejectedhas now become the cornerstone.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>This is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s doing,and it is wonderful to see.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>This is the day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has made.We will rejoice and be glad in it.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Please, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, please save us.Please, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, please give us success.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Bless the one who comes in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.We bless you from the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is God, shining upon us.Take the sacrifice and bind it with cords on the altar.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>You are my God, and I will praise you!You are my God, and I will exalt you!",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Give thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for he is good!His faithful love endures forever."
		},
		"119": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Joyful are people of integrity,who follow the instructions of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Joyful are those who obey his lawsand search for him with all their hearts.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They do not compromise with evil,and they walk only in his paths.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You have charged usto keep your commandments carefully.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Oh, that my actions would consistentlyreflect your decrees!",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then I will not be ashamedwhen I compare my life with your commands.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>As I learn your righteous regulations,I will thank you by living as I should!",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I will obey your decrees.Please don’t give up on me!",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>How can a young person stay pure?By obeying your word.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>I have tried hard to find you—don’t let me wander from your commands.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>I have hidden your word in my heart,that I might not sin against you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>I praise you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;teach me your decrees.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I have recited aloudall the regulations you have given us.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>I have rejoiced in your lawsas much as in riches.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>I will study your commandmentsand reflect on your ways.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>I will delight in your decreesand not forget your word.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Be good to your servant,that I may live and obey your word.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Open my eyes to seethe wonderful truths in your instructions.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>I am only a foreigner in the land.Don’t hide your commands from me!",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>I am always overwhelmedwith a desire for your regulations.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>You rebuke the arrogant;those who wander from your commands are cursed.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Don’t let them scorn and insult me,for I have obeyed your laws.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Even princes sit and speak against me,but I will meditate on your decrees.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Your laws please me;they give me wise advice.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>I lie in the dust;revive me by your word.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>I told you my plans, and you answered.Now teach me your decrees.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Help me understand the meaning of your commandments,and I will meditate on your wonderful deeds.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>I weep with sorrow;encourage me by your word.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Keep me from lying to myself;give me the privilege of knowing your instructions.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>I have chosen to be faithful;I have determined to live by your regulations.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>I cling to your laws.<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, don’t let me be put to shame!",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>I will pursue your commands,for you expand my understanding.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Teach me your decrees, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;I will keep them to the end.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Give me understanding and I will obey your instructions;I will put them into practice with all my heart.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Make me walk along the path of your commands,for that is where my happiness is found.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Give me an eagerness for your lawsrather than a love for money!",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Turn my eyes from worthless things,and give me life through your word.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Reassure me of your promise,made to those who fear you.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Help me abandon my shameful ways;for your regulations are good.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>I long to obey your commandments!Renew my life with your goodness.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, give me your unfailing love,the salvation that you promised me.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Then I can answer those who taunt me,for I trust in your word.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Do not snatch your word of truth from me,for your regulations are my only hope.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>I will keep on obeying your instructionsforever and ever.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>I will walk in freedom,for I have devoted myself to your commandments.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>I will speak to kings about your laws,and I will not be ashamed.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>How I delight in your commands!How I love them!",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>I honor and love your commands.I meditate on your decrees.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Remember your promise to me;it is my only hope.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Your promise revives me;it comforts me in all my troubles.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>The proud hold me in utter contempt,but I do not turn away from your instructions.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>I meditate on your age-old regulations;O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, they comfort me.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>I become furious with the wicked,because they reject your instructions.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>Your decrees have been the theme of my songswherever I have lived.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>I reflect at night on who you are, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;therefore, I obey your instructions.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>This is how I spend my life:obeying your commandments.",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you are mine!I promise to obey your words!",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>With all my heart I want your blessings.Be merciful as you promised.",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>I pondered the direction of my life,and I turned to follow your laws.",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>I will hurry, without delay,to obey your commands.",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>Evil people try to drag me into sin,but I am firmly anchored to your instructions.",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>I rise at midnight to thank youfor your just regulations.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>I am a friend to anyone who fears you—anyone who obeys your commandments.",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, your unfailing love fills the earth;teach me your decrees.",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>You have done many good things for me, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,just as you promised.",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup>I believe in your commands;now teach me good judgment and knowledge.",
			"67": "<sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup>I used to wander off until you disciplined me;but now I closely follow your word.",
			"68": "<sup class=\"versenum\">68 </sup>You are good and do only good;teach me your decrees.",
			"69": "<sup class=\"versenum\">69 </sup>Arrogant people smear me with lies,but in truth I obey your commandments with all my heart.",
			"70": "<sup class=\"versenum\">70 </sup>Their hearts are dull and stupid,but I delight in your instructions.",
			"71": "<sup class=\"versenum\">71 </sup>My suffering was good for me,for it taught me to pay attention to your decrees.",
			"72": "<sup class=\"versenum\">72 </sup>Your instructions are more valuable to methan millions in gold and silver.",
			"73": "<sup class=\"versenum\">73 </sup>You made me; you created me.Now give me the sense to follow your commands.",
			"74": "<sup class=\"versenum\">74 </sup>May all who fear you find in me a cause for joy,for I have put my hope in your word.",
			"75": "<sup class=\"versenum\">75 </sup>I know, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that your regulations are fair;you disciplined me because I needed it.",
			"76": "<sup class=\"versenum\">76 </sup>Now let your unfailing love comfort me,just as you promised me, your servant.",
			"77": "<sup class=\"versenum\">77 </sup>Surround me with your tender mercies so I may live,for your instructions are my delight.",
			"78": "<sup class=\"versenum\">78 </sup>Bring disgrace upon the arrogant people who lied about me;meanwhile, I will concentrate on your commandments.",
			"79": "<sup class=\"versenum\">79 </sup>Let me be united with all who fear you,with those who know your laws.",
			"80": "<sup class=\"versenum\">80 </sup>May I be blameless in keeping your decrees;then I will never be ashamed.",
			"81": "<sup class=\"versenum\">81 </sup>I am worn out waiting for your rescue,but I have put my hope in your word.",
			"82": "<sup class=\"versenum\">82 </sup>My eyes are straining to see your promises come true.When will you comfort me?",
			"83": "<sup class=\"versenum\">83 </sup>I am shriveled like a wineskin in the smoke,but I have not forgotten to obey your decrees.",
			"84": "<sup class=\"versenum\">84 </sup>How long must I wait?When will you punish those who persecute me?",
			"85": "<sup class=\"versenum\">85 </sup>These arrogant people who hate your instructionshave dug deep pits to trap me.",
			"86": "<sup class=\"versenum\">86 </sup>All your commands are trustworthy.Protect me from those who hunt me down without cause.",
			"87": "<sup class=\"versenum\">87 </sup>They almost finished me off,but I refused to abandon your commandments.",
			"88": "<sup class=\"versenum\">88 </sup>In your unfailing love, spare my life;then I can continue to obey your laws.",
			"89": "<sup class=\"versenum\">89 </sup>Your eternal word, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,stands firm in heaven.",
			"90": "<sup class=\"versenum\">90 </sup>Your faithfulness extends to every generation,as enduring as the earth you created.",
			"91": "<sup class=\"versenum\">91 </sup>Your regulations remain true to this day,for everything serves your plans.",
			"92": "<sup class=\"versenum\">92 </sup>If your instructions hadn’t sustained me with joy,I would have died in my misery.",
			"93": "<sup class=\"versenum\">93 </sup>I will never forget your commandments,for by them you give me life.",
			"94": "<sup class=\"versenum\">94 </sup>I am yours; rescue me!For I have worked hard at obeying your commandments.",
			"95": "<sup class=\"versenum\">95 </sup>Though the wicked hide along the way to kill me,I will quietly keep my mind on your laws.",
			"96": "<sup class=\"versenum\">96 </sup>Even perfection has its limits,but your commands have no limit.",
			"97": "<sup class=\"versenum\">97 </sup>Oh, how I love your instructions!I think about them all day long.",
			"98": "<sup class=\"versenum\">98 </sup>Your commands make me wiser than my enemies,for they are my constant guide.",
			"99": "<sup class=\"versenum\">99 </sup>Yes, I have more insight than my teachers,for I am always thinking of your laws.",
			"100": "<sup class=\"versenum\">100 </sup>I am even wiser than my elders,for I have kept your commandments.",
			"101": "<sup class=\"versenum\">101 </sup>I have refused to walk on any evil path,so that I may remain obedient to your word.",
			"102": "<sup class=\"versenum\">102 </sup>I haven’t turned away from your regulations,for you have taught me well.",
			"103": "<sup class=\"versenum\">103 </sup>How sweet your words taste to me;they are sweeter than honey.",
			"104": "<sup class=\"versenum\">104 </sup>Your commandments give me understanding;no wonder I hate every false way of life.",
			"105": "<sup class=\"versenum\">105 </sup>Your word is a lamp to guide my feetand a light for my path.",
			"106": "<sup class=\"versenum\">106 </sup>I’ve promised it once, and I’ll promise it again:I will obey your righteous regulations.",
			"107": "<sup class=\"versenum\">107 </sup>I have suffered much, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;restore my life again as you promised.",
			"108": "<sup class=\"versenum\">108 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, accept my offering of praise,and teach me your regulations.",
			"109": "<sup class=\"versenum\">109 </sup>My life constantly hangs in the balance,but I will not stop obeying your instructions.",
			"110": "<sup class=\"versenum\">110 </sup>The wicked have set their traps for me,but I will not turn from your commandments.",
			"111": "<sup class=\"versenum\">111 </sup>Your laws are my treasure;they are my heart’s delight.",
			"112": "<sup class=\"versenum\">112 </sup>I am determined to keep your decreesto the very end.",
			"113": "<sup class=\"versenum\">113 </sup>I hate those with divided loyalties,but I love your instructions.",
			"114": "<sup class=\"versenum\">114 </sup>You are my refuge and my shield;your word is my source of hope.",
			"115": "<sup class=\"versenum\">115 </sup>Get out of my life, you evil-minded people,for I intend to obey the commands of my God.",
			"116": "<sup class=\"versenum\">116 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, sustain me as you promised, that I may live!Do not let my hope be crushed.",
			"117": "<sup class=\"versenum\">117 </sup>Sustain me, and I will be rescued;then I will meditate continually on your decrees.",
			"118": "<sup class=\"versenum\">118 </sup>But you have rejected all who stray from your decrees.They are only fooling themselves.",
			"119": "<sup class=\"versenum\">119 </sup>You skim off the wicked of the earth like scum;no wonder I love to obey your laws!",
			"120": "<sup class=\"versenum\">120 </sup>I tremble in fear of you;I stand in awe of your regulations.",
			"121": "<sup class=\"versenum\">121 </sup>Don’t leave me to the mercy of my enemies,for I have done what is just and right.",
			"122": "<sup class=\"versenum\">122 </sup>Please guarantee a blessing for me.Don’t let the arrogant oppress me!",
			"123": "<sup class=\"versenum\">123 </sup>My eyes strain to see your rescue,to see the truth of your promise fulfilled.",
			"124": "<sup class=\"versenum\">124 </sup>I am your servant; deal with me in unfailing love,and teach me your decrees.",
			"125": "<sup class=\"versenum\">125 </sup>Give discernment to me, your servant;then I will understand your laws.",
			"126": "<sup class=\"versenum\">126 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, it is time for you to act,for these evil people have violated your instructions.",
			"127": "<sup class=\"versenum\">127 </sup>Truly, I love your commandsmore than gold, even the finest gold.",
			"128": "<sup class=\"versenum\">128 </sup>Each of your commandments is right.That is why I hate every false way.",
			"129": "<sup class=\"versenum\">129 </sup>Your laws are wonderful.No wonder I obey them!",
			"130": "<sup class=\"versenum\">130 </sup>The teaching of your word gives light,so even the simple can understand.",
			"131": "<sup class=\"versenum\">131 </sup>I pant with expectation,longing for your commands.",
			"132": "<sup class=\"versenum\">132 </sup>Come and show me your mercy,as you do for all who love your name.",
			"133": "<sup class=\"versenum\">133 </sup>Guide my steps by your word,so I will not be overcome by evil.",
			"134": "<sup class=\"versenum\">134 </sup>Ransom me from the oppression of evil people;then I can obey your commandments.",
			"135": "<sup class=\"versenum\">135 </sup>Look upon me with love;teach me your decrees.",
			"136": "<sup class=\"versenum\">136 </sup>Rivers of tears gush from my eyesbecause people disobey your instructions.",
			"137": "<sup class=\"versenum\">137 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you are righteous,and your regulations are fair.",
			"138": "<sup class=\"versenum\">138 </sup>Your laws are perfectand completely trustworthy.",
			"139": "<sup class=\"versenum\">139 </sup>I am overwhelmed with indignation,for my enemies have disregarded your words.",
			"140": "<sup class=\"versenum\">140 </sup>Your promises have been thoroughly tested;that is why I love them so much.",
			"141": "<sup class=\"versenum\">141 </sup>I am insignificant and despised,but I don’t forget your commandments.",
			"142": "<sup class=\"versenum\">142 </sup>Your justice is eternal,and your instructions are perfectly true.",
			"143": "<sup class=\"versenum\">143 </sup>As pressure and stress bear down on me,I find joy in your commands.",
			"144": "<sup class=\"versenum\">144 </sup>Your laws are always right;help me to understand them so I may live.",
			"145": "<sup class=\"versenum\">145 </sup>I pray with all my heart; answer me, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!I will obey your decrees.",
			"146": "<sup class=\"versenum\">146 </sup>I cry out to you; rescue me,that I may obey your laws.",
			"147": "<sup class=\"versenum\">147 </sup>I rise early, before the sun is up;I cry out for help and put my hope in your words.",
			"148": "<sup class=\"versenum\">148 </sup>I stay awake through the night,thinking about your promise.",
			"149": "<sup class=\"versenum\">149 </sup>In your faithful love, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, hear my cry;let me be revived by following your regulations.",
			"150": "<sup class=\"versenum\">150 </sup>Lawless people are coming to attack me;they live far from your instructions.",
			"151": "<sup class=\"versenum\">151 </sup>But you are near, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,and all your commands are true.",
			"152": "<sup class=\"versenum\">152 </sup>I have known from my earliest daysthat your laws will last forever.",
			"153": "<sup class=\"versenum\">153 </sup>Look upon my suffering and rescue me,for I have not forgotten your instructions.",
			"154": "<sup class=\"versenum\">154 </sup>Argue my case; take my side!Protect my life as you promised.",
			"155": "<sup class=\"versenum\">155 </sup>The wicked are far from rescue,for they do not bother with your decrees.",
			"156": "<sup class=\"versenum\">156 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, how great is your mercy;let me be revived by following your regulations.",
			"157": "<sup class=\"versenum\">157 </sup>Many persecute and trouble me,yet I have not swerved from your laws.",
			"158": "<sup class=\"versenum\">158 </sup>Seeing these traitors makes me sick at heart,because they care nothing for your word.",
			"159": "<sup class=\"versenum\">159 </sup>See how I love your commandments, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.Give back my life because of your unfailing love.",
			"160": "<sup class=\"versenum\">160 </sup>The very essence of your words is truth;all your just regulations will stand forever.",
			"161": "<sup class=\"versenum\">161 </sup>Powerful people harass me without cause,but my heart trembles only at your word.",
			"162": "<sup class=\"versenum\">162 </sup>I rejoice in your wordlike one who discovers a great treasure.",
			"163": "<sup class=\"versenum\">163 </sup>I hate and abhor all falsehood,but I love your instructions.",
			"164": "<sup class=\"versenum\">164 </sup>I will praise you seven times a daybecause all your regulations are just.",
			"165": "<sup class=\"versenum\">165 </sup>Those who love your instructions have great peaceand do not stumble.",
			"166": "<sup class=\"versenum\">166 </sup>I long for your rescue, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,so I have obeyed your commands.",
			"167": "<sup class=\"versenum\">167 </sup>I have obeyed your laws,for I love them very much.",
			"168": "<sup class=\"versenum\">168 </sup>Yes, I obey your commandments and lawsbecause you know everything I do.",
			"169": "<sup class=\"versenum\">169 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, listen to my cry;give me the discerning mind you promised.",
			"170": "<sup class=\"versenum\">170 </sup>Listen to my prayer;rescue me as you promised.",
			"171": "<sup class=\"versenum\">171 </sup>Let praise flow from my lips,for you have taught me your decrees.",
			"172": "<sup class=\"versenum\">172 </sup>Let my tongue sing about your word,for all your commands are right.",
			"173": "<sup class=\"versenum\">173 </sup>Give me a helping hand,for I have chosen to follow your commandments.",
			"174": "<sup class=\"versenum\">174 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, I have longed for your rescue,and your instructions are my delight.",
			"175": "<sup class=\"versenum\">175 </sup>Let me live so I can praise you,and may your regulations help me.",
			"176": "<sup class=\"versenum\">176 </sup>I have wandered away like a lost sheep;come and find me,for I have not forgotten your commands."
		},
		"120": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>I took my troubles to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;I cried out to him, and he answered my prayer.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Rescue me, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, from liarsand from all deceitful people.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>O deceptive tongue, what will God do to you?How will he increase your punishment?",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You will be pierced with sharp arrowsand burned with glowing coals.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>How I suffer in far-off Meshech.It pains me to live in distant Kedar.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I am tired of livingamong people who hate peace.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I search for peace;but when I speak of peace, they want war!"
		},
		"121": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>I look up to the mountains—does my help come from there?",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>My help comes from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,who made heaven and earth!",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He will not let you stumble;the one who watches over you will not slumber.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Indeed, he who watches over Israelnever slumbers or sleeps.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> himself watches over you!The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> stands beside you as your protective shade.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The sun will not harm you by day,nor the moon at night.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> keeps you from all harmand watches over your life.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> keeps watch over you as you come and go,both now and forever."
		},
		"122": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>I was glad when they said to me,“Let us go to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And now here we are,standing inside your gates, O Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Jerusalem is a well-built city;its seamless walls cannot be breached.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>All the tribes of Israel—the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s people—make their pilgrimage here.They come to give thanks to the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,as the law requires of Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Here stand the thrones where judgment is given,the thrones of the dynasty of David.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Pray for peace in Jerusalem.May all who love this city prosper.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>O Jerusalem, may there be peace within your wallsand prosperity in your palaces.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>For the sake of my family and friends, I will say,“May you have peace.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For the sake of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God,I will seek what is best for you, O Jerusalem."
		},
		"123": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>I lift my eyes to you,O God, enthroned in heaven.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>We keep looking to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God for his mercy,just as servants keep their eyes on their master,as a slave girl watches her mistress for the slightest signal.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Have mercy on us, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, have mercy,for we have had our fill of contempt.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>We have had more than our fill of the scoffing of the proudand the contempt of the arrogant."
		},
		"124": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>What if the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had not been on our side?Let all Israel repeat:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>What if the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had not been on our sidewhen people attacked us?",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They would have swallowed us alivein their burning anger.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The waters would have engulfed us;a torrent would have overwhelmed us.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Yes, the raging waters of their furywould have overwhelmed our very lives.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,who did not let their teeth tear us apart!",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>We escaped like a bird from a hunter’s trap.The trap is broken, and we are free!",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Our help is from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,who made heaven and earth."
		},
		"125": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Those who trust in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> are as secure as Mount Zion;they will not be defeated but will endure forever.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Just as the mountains surround Jerusalem,so the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> surrounds his people, both now and forever.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The wicked will not rule the land of the godly,for then the godly might be tempted to do wrong.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, do good to those who are good,whose hearts are in tune with you.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But banish those who turn to crooked ways, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.Take them away with those who do evil.May Israel have peace!"
		},
		"126": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought back his exiles to Jerusalem,it was like a dream!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>We were filled with laughter,and we sang for joy.And the other nations said,“What amazing things the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has done for them.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Yes, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has done amazing things for us!What joy!",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Restore our fortunes, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,as streams renew the desert.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Those who plant in tearswill harvest with shouts of joy.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They weep as they go to plant their seed,but they sing as they return with the harvest."
		},
		"127": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Unless the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> builds a house,the work of the builders is wasted.Unless the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> protects a city,guarding it with sentries will do no good.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>It is useless for you to work so hardfrom early morning until late at night,anxiously working for food to eat;for God gives rest to his loved ones.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Children are a gift from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;they are a reward from him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Children born to a young manare like arrows in a warrior’s hands.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>How joyful is the man whose quiver is full of them!He will not be put to shame when he confronts his accusers at the city gates."
		},
		"128": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>How joyful are those who fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—all who follow his ways!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>You will enjoy the fruit of your labor.How joyful and prosperous you will be!",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Your wife will be like a fruitful grapevine,flourishing within your home.Your children will be like vigorous young olive treesas they sit around your table.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>That is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s blessingfor those who fear him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> continually bless you from Zion.May you see Jerusalem prosper as long as you live.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>May you live to enjoy your grandchildren.May Israel have peace!"
		},
		"129": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>From my earliest youth my enemies have persecuted me.Let all Israel repeat this:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>From my earliest youth my enemies have persecuted me,but they have never defeated me.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>My back is covered with cuts,as if a farmer had plowed long furrows.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is good;he has cut me free from the ropes of the ungodly.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>May all who hate Jerusalembe turned back in shameful defeat.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>May they be as useless as grass on a rooftop,turning yellow when only half grown,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>ignored by the harvester,despised by the binder.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And may those who pass byrefuse to give them this blessing:“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> bless you;we bless you in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s name.”"
		},
		"130": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>From the depths of despair, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,I call for your help.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Hear my cry, O Lord.Pay attention to my prayer.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, if you kept a record of our sins,who, O Lord, could ever survive?",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But you offer forgiveness,that we might learn to fear you.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I am counting on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;yes, I am counting on him.I have put my hope in his word.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I long for the Lordmore than sentries long for the dawn,yes, more than sentries long for the dawn.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>O Israel, hope in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;for with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> there is unfailing love.His redemption overflows.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He himself will redeem Israelfrom every kind of sin."
		},
		"131": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, my heart is not proud;my eyes are not haughty.I don’t concern myself with matters too greator too awesome for me to grasp.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Instead, I have calmed and quieted myself,like a weaned child who no longer cries for its mother’s milk.Yes, like a weaned child is my soul within me.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>O Israel, put your hope in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—now and always."
		},
		"132": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, remember Davidand all that he suffered.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He made a solemn promise to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.He vowed to the Mighty One of Israel,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“I will not go home;I will not let myself rest.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I will not let my eyes sleepnor close my eyelids in slumber",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>until I find a place to build a house for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,a sanctuary for the Mighty One of Israel.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>We heard that the Ark was in Ephrathah;then we found it in the distant countryside of Jaar.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Let us go to the sanctuary of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;let us worship at the footstool of his throne.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Arise, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and enter your resting place,along with the Ark, the symbol of your power.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>May your priests be clothed in godliness;may your loyal servants sing for joy.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For the sake of your servant David,do not reject the king you have anointed.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> swore an oath to Davidwith a promise he will never take back:“I will place one of your descendantson your throne.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>If your descendants obey the terms of my covenantand the laws that I teach them,then your royal linewill continue forever and ever.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has chosen Jerusalem;he has desired it for his home.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“This is my resting place forever,” he said.“I will live here, for this is the home I desired.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>I will bless this city and make it prosperous;I will satisfy its poor with food.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>I will clothe its priests with godliness;its faithful servants will sing for joy.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Here I will increase the power of David;my anointed one will be a light for my people.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>I will clothe his enemies with shame,but he will be a glorious king.”"
		},
		"133": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>How wonderful and pleasant it iswhen brothers live together in harmony!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>For harmony is as precious as the anointing oilthat was poured over Aaron’s head,that ran down his beardand onto the border of his robe.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Harmony is as refreshing as the dew from Mount Hermonthat falls on the mountains of Zion.And there the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has pronounced his blessing,even life everlasting."
		},
		"134": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Oh, praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, all you servants of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,you who serve at night in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Lift your hands toward the sanctuary,and praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who made heaven and earth,bless you from Jerusalem."
		},
		"135": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!Praise the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!Praise him, you who serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>you who serve in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,in the courts of the house of our God.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is good;celebrate his lovely name with music.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has chosen Jacob for himself,Israel for his own special treasure.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I know the greatness of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—that our Lord is greater than any other god.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> does whatever pleases himthroughout all heaven and earth,and on the seas and in their depths.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He causes the clouds to rise over the whole earth.He sends the lightning with the rainand releases the wind from his storehouses.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He destroyed the firstborn in each Egyptian home,both people and animals.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He performed miraculous signs and wonders in Egyptagainst Pharaoh and all his people.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He struck down great nationsand slaughtered mighty kings—",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Sihon king of the Amorites,Og king of Bashan,and all the kings of Canaan.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He gave their land as an inheritance,a special possession to his people Israel.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Your name, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, endures forever;your fame, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, is known to every generation.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will give justice to his peopleand have compassion on his servants.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The idols of the nations are merely things of silver and gold,shaped by human hands.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>They have mouths but cannot speak,and eyes but cannot see.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They have ears but cannot hear,and mouths but cannot breathe.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And those who make idols are just like them,as are all who trust in them.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>O Israel, praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!O priests—descendants of Aaron—praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>O Levites, praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!All you who fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be praised from Zion,for he lives here in Jerusalem.Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!"
		},
		"136": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Give thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for he is good!<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Give thanks to the God of gods.<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Give thanks to the Lord of lords.<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Give thanks to him who alone does mighty miracles.<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Give thanks to him who made the heavens so skillfully.<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Give thanks to him who placed the earth among the waters.<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Give thanks to him who made the heavenly lights—<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>the sun to rule the day,<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and the moon and stars to rule the night.<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Give thanks to him who killed the firstborn of Egypt.<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He brought Israel out of Egypt.<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He acted with a strong hand and powerful arm.<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Give thanks to him who parted the Red Sea.<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He led Israel safely through,<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>but he hurled Pharaoh and his army into the Red Sea.<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Give thanks to him who led his people through the wilderness.<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Give thanks to him who struck down mighty kings.<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He killed powerful kings—<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Sihon king of the Amorites,<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and Og king of Bashan.<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>God gave the land of these kings as an inheritance—<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>a special possession to his servant Israel.<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He remembered us in our weakness.<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He saved us from our enemies.<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He gives food to every living thing.<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Give thanks to the God of heaven.<i>His faithful love endures forever.</i>"
		},
		"137": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Beside the rivers of Babylon, we sat and weptas we thought of Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>We put away our harps,hanging them on the branches of poplar trees.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For our captors demanded a song from us.Our tormentors insisted on a joyful hymn:“Sing us one of those songs of Jerusalem!”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But how can we sing the songs of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>while in a pagan land?",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>If I forget you, O Jerusalem,let my right hand forget how to play the harp.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>May my tongue stick to the roof of my mouthif I fail to remember you,if I don’t make Jerusalem my greatest joy.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, remember what the Edomites didon the day the armies of Babylon captured Jerusalem.“Destroy it!” they yelled.“Level it to the ground!”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>O Babylon, you will be destroyed.Happy is the one who pays you backfor what you have done to us.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Happy is the one who takes your babiesand smashes them against the rocks!"
		},
		"138": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>I give you thanks, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, with all my heart;I will sing your praises before the gods.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I bow before your holy Temple as I worship.I praise your name for your unfailing love and faithfulness;for your promises are backedby all the honor of your name.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>As soon as I pray, you answer me;you encourage me by giving me strength.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Every king in all the earth will thank you, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,for all of them will hear your words.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Yes, they will sing about the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s ways,for the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is very great.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Though the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is great, he cares for the humble,but he keeps his distance from the proud.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Though I am surrounded by troubles,you will protect me from the anger of my enemies.You reach out your hand,and the power of your right hand saves me.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will work out his plans for my life—for your faithful love, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, endures forever.Don’t abandon me, for you made me."
		},
		"139": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you have examined my heartand know everything about me.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>You know when I sit down or stand up.You know my thoughts even when I’m far away.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You see me when I traveland when I rest at home.You know everything I do.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You know what I am going to sayeven before I say it, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You go before me and follow me.You place your hand of blessing on my head.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Such knowledge is too wonderful for me,too great for me to understand!",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I can never escape from your Spirit!I can never get away from your presence!",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>If I go up to heaven, you are there;if I go down to the grave, you are there.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>If I ride the wings of the morning,if I dwell by the farthest oceans,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>even there your hand will guide me,and your strength will support me.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>I could ask the darkness to hide meand the light around me to become night—",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>but even in darkness I cannot hide from you.To you the night shines as bright as day.Darkness and light are the same to you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>You made all the delicate, inner parts of my bodyand knit me together in my mother’s womb.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Thank you for making me so wonderfully complex!Your workmanship is marvelous—how well I know it.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>You watched me as I was being formed in utter seclusion,as I was woven together in the dark of the womb.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>You saw me before I was born.Every day of my life was recorded in your book.Every moment was laid outbefore a single day had passed.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>How precious are your thoughts about me, O God.They cannot be numbered!",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>I can’t even count them;they outnumber the grains of sand!And when I wake up,you are still with me!",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>O God, if only you would destroy the wicked!Get out of my life, you murderers!",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>They blaspheme you;your enemies misuse your name.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, shouldn’t I hate those who hate you?Shouldn’t I despise those who oppose you?",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Yes, I hate them with total hatred,for your enemies are my enemies.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Search me, O God, and know my heart;test me and know my anxious thoughts.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Point out anything in me that offends you,and lead me along the path of everlasting life."
		},
		"140": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, rescue me from evil people.Protect me from those who are violent,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>those who plot evil in their heartsand stir up trouble all day long.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Their tongues sting like a snake;the venom of a viper drips from their lips. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, keep me out of the hands of the wicked.Protect me from those who are violent,for they are plotting against me.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The proud have set a trap to catch me;they have stretched out a net;they have placed traps all along the way. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “You are my God!”Listen, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to my cries for mercy!",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>O Sovereign <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the strong one who rescued me,you protected me on the day of battle.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, do not let evil people have their way.Do not let their evil schemes succeed,or they will become proud. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Let my enemies be destroyedby the very evil they have planned for me.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Let burning coals fall down on their heads.Let them be thrown into the fireor into watery pits from which they can’t escape.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Don’t let liars prosper here in our land.Cause great disasters to fall on the violent.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But I know the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will help those they persecute;he will give justice to the poor.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Surely righteous people are praising your name;the godly will live in your presence."
		},
		"141": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, I am calling to you. Please hurry!Listen when I cry to you for help!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Accept my prayer as incense offered to you,and my upraised hands as an evening offering.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Take control of what I say, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,and guard my lips.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Don’t let me drift toward evilor take part in acts of wickedness.Don’t let me share in the delicaciesof those who do wrong.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Let the godly strike me!It will be a kindness!If they correct me, it is soothing medicine.Don’t let me refuse it.But I pray constantlyagainst the wicked and their deeds.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When their leaders are thrown down from a cliff,the wicked will listen to my words and find them true.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Like rocks brought up by a plow,the bones of the wicked will lie scattered without burial.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I look to you for help, O Sovereign <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.You are my refuge; don’t let them kill me.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Keep me from the traps they have set for me,from the snares of those who do wrong.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Let the wicked fall into their own nets,but let me escape."
		},
		"142": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>I cry out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;I plead for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s mercy.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I pour out my complaints before himand tell him all my troubles.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When I am overwhelmed,you alone know the way I should turn.Wherever I go,my enemies have set traps for me.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I look for someone to come and help me,but no one gives me a passing thought!No one will help me;no one cares a bit what happens to me.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then I pray to you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.I say, “You are my place of refuge.You are all I really want in life.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Hear my cry,for I am very low.Rescue me from my persecutors,for they are too strong for me.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Bring me out of prisonso I can thank you.The godly will crowd around me,for you are good to me.”"
		},
		"143": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Hear my prayer, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;listen to my plea!Answer me because you are faithful and righteous.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Don’t put your servant on trial,for no one is innocent before you.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>My enemy has chased me.He has knocked me to the groundand forces me to live in darkness like those in the grave.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I am losing all hope;I am paralyzed with fear.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I remember the days of old.I ponder all your great worksand think about what you have done.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I lift my hands to you in prayer.I thirst for you as parched land thirsts for rain. <span class=\"selah\">Interlude</span>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Come quickly, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and answer me,for my depression deepens.Don’t turn away from me,or I will die.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Let me hear of your unfailing love each morning,for I am trusting you.Show me where to walk,for I give myself to you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Rescue me from my enemies, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;I run to you to hide me.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Teach me to do your will,for you are my God.May your gracious Spirit lead me forwardon a firm footing.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>For the glory of your name, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, preserve my life.Because of your faithfulness, bring me out of this distress.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>In your unfailing love, silence all my enemiesand destroy all my foes,for I am your servant."
		},
		"144": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who is my rock.He trains my hands for warand gives my fingers skill for battle.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He is my loving ally and my fortress,my tower of safety, my rescuer.He is my shield, and I take refuge in him.He makes the nations submit to me.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, what are human beings that you should notice them,mere mortals that you should think about them?",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For they are like a breath of air;their days are like a passing shadow.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Open the heavens, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and come down.Touch the mountains so they billow smoke.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Hurl your lightning bolts and scatter your enemies!Shoot your arrows and confuse them!",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Reach down from heaven and rescue me;rescue me from deep waters,from the power of my enemies.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Their mouths are full of lies;they swear to tell the truth, but they lie instead.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>I will sing a new song to you, O God!I will sing your praises with a ten-stringed harp.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For you grant victory to kings!You rescued your servant David from the fatal sword.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Save me!Rescue me from the power of my enemies.Their mouths are full of lies;they swear to tell the truth, but they lie instead.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>May our sons flourish in their youthlike well-nurtured plants.May our daughters be like graceful pillars,carved to beautify a palace.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>May our barns be filledwith crops of every kind.May the flocks in our fields multiply by the thousands,even tens of thousands,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>and may our oxen be loaded down with produce.May there be no enemy breaking through our walls,no going into captivity,no cries of alarm in our town squares.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Yes, joyful are those who live like this!Joyful indeed are those whose God is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"145": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>I will exalt you, my God and King,and praise your name forever and ever.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I will praise you every day;yes, I will praise you forever.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Great is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>! He is most worthy of praise!No one can measure his greatness.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Let each generation tell its children of your mighty acts;let them proclaim your power.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I will meditate on your majestic, glorious splendorand your wonderful miracles.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Your awe-inspiring deeds will be on every tongue;I will proclaim your greatness.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Everyone will share the story of your wonderful goodness;they will sing with joy about your righteousness.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is merciful and compassionate,slow to get angry and filled with unfailing love.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is good to everyone.He showers compassion on all his creation.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>All of your works will thank you, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,and your faithful followers will praise you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They will speak of the glory of your kingdom;they will give examples of your power.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They will tell about your mighty deedsand about the majesty and glory of your reign.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>For your kingdom is an everlasting kingdom.You rule throughout all generations.The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> always keeps his promises;he is gracious in all he does.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> helps the fallenand lifts those bent beneath their loads.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The eyes of all look to you in hope;you give them their food as they need it.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When you open your hand,you satisfy the hunger and thirst of every living thing.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is righteous in everything he does;he is filled with kindness.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is close to all who call on him,yes, to all who call on him in truth.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He grants the desires of those who fear him;he hears their cries for help and rescues them.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> protects all those who love him,but he destroys the wicked.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>I will praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,and may everyone on earth bless his holy nameforever and ever."
		},
		"146": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!Let all that I am praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>I will praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as long as I live.I will sing praises to my God with my dying breath.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Don’t put your confidence in powerful people;there is no help for you there.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When they breathe their last, they return to the earth,and all their plans die with them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But joyful are those who have the God of Israel as their helper,whose hope is in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He made heaven and earth,the sea, and everything in them.He keeps every promise forever.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He gives justice to the oppressedand food to the hungry.The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> frees the prisoners.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> opens the eyes of the blind.The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lifts up those who are weighed down.The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> loves the godly.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> protects the foreigners among us.He cares for the orphans and widows,but he frustrates the plans of the wicked.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will reign forever.He will be your God, O Jerusalem, throughout the generations.Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!"
		},
		"147": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!How good to sing praises to our God!How delightful and how fitting!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is rebuilding Jerusalemand bringing the exiles back to Israel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He heals the brokenheartedand bandages their wounds.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He counts the starsand calls them all by name.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>How great is our Lord! His power is absolute!His understanding is beyond comprehension!",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> supports the humble,but he brings the wicked down into the dust.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Sing out your thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;sing praises to our God with a harp.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He covers the heavens with clouds,provides rain for the earth,and makes the grass grow in mountain pastures.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He gives food to the wild animalsand feeds the young ravens when they cry.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He takes no pleasure in the strength of a horseor in human might.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>No, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s delight is in those who fear him,those who put their hope in his unfailing love.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Glorify the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, O Jerusalem!Praise your God, O Zion!",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>For he has strengthened the bars of your gatesand blessed your children within your walls.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He sends peace across your nationand satisfies your hunger with the finest wheat.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He sends his orders to the world—how swiftly his word flies!",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He sends the snow like white wool;he scatters frost upon the ground like ashes.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He hurls the hail like stones.Who can stand against his freezing cold?",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then, at his command, it all melts.He sends his winds, and the ice thaws.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He has revealed his words to Jacob,his decrees and regulations to Israel.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He has not done this for any other nation;they do not know his regulations.Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!"
		},
		"148": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> from the heavens!Praise him from the skies!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Praise him, all his angels!Praise him, all the armies of heaven!",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Praise him, sun and moon!Praise him, all you twinkling stars!",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Praise him, skies above!Praise him, vapors high above the clouds!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Let every created thing give praise to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,for he issued his command, and they came into being.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He set them in place forever and ever.His decree will never be revoked.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> from the earth,you creatures of the ocean depths,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>fire and hail, snow and clouds,wind and weather that obey him,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>mountains and all hills,fruit trees and all cedars,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>wild animals and all livestock,small scurrying animals and birds,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>kings of the earth and all people,rulers and judges of the earth,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>young men and young women,old men and children.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Let them all praise the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.For his name is very great;his glory towers over the earth and heaven!",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He has made his people strong,honoring his faithful ones—the people of Israel who are close to him.Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!"
		},
		"149": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!Sing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> a new song.Sing his praises in the assembly of the faithful.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>O Israel, rejoice in your Maker.O people of Jerusalem, exult in your King.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Praise his name with dancing,accompanied by tambourine and harp.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> delights in his people;he crowns the humble with victory.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Let the faithful rejoice that he honors them.Let them sing for joy as they lie on their beds.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Let the praises of God be in their mouths,and a sharp sword in their hands—",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>to execute vengeance on the nationsand punishment on the peoples,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>to bind their kings with shacklesand their leaders with iron chains,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>to execute the judgment written against them.This is the glorious privilege of his faithful ones.Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!"
		},
		"150": {
			"1": "<sup class=\"versenum\">1 </sup>Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!Praise God in his sanctuary;praise him in his mighty heaven!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Praise him for his mighty works;praise his unequaled greatness!",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Praise him with a blast of the ram’s horn;praise him with the lyre and harp!",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Praise him with the tambourine and dancing;praise him with strings and flutes!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Praise him with a clash of cymbals;praise him with loud clanging cymbals.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Let everything that breathes sing praises to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!"
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;